{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783744105843,"sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ZpBMu8QdrXX78uxhEoHLqC7D","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","offset":1,"limit":500},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: # DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: # YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n5: # - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n6: #   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n7: #   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n8: # - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n9: #   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n10: #   free-form narrative prose.\n11: # - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n12: #   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n13: #\n14: # GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n15: # - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n16: #   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n17: #   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n18: #   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n19: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n20: role: Deep Research Loop Manager\n21: purpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\n22: action: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\n23: operating_mode:\n24:   workflow: iterative_loop\n25:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n26:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n27:   approvals: none\n28:   tracking: progressive_research_state\n29:   validation: convergence_detection\n30: \n31: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n32: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n33: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n34: operating_principles:\n35:   core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n36:   approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n37:   mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n38: \n39: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n40: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n41: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n42: user_inputs:\n43:   research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n44:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n45:   max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n46:   convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n47:   convergence_mode: \"[default|off|sliding-window|divergent] - Convergence policy modifier. Default: default.\"\n48: \n49: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n50: # CONTEXT LOADING\n51: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n52: context_loading:\n53:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n54:   purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n55:   mcp_integration:\n56:     tool: memory_context\n57:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n58:     parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n59:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n60:   behavior:\n61:     if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n62:     if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n63: \n64: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n65: # SKILL REFERENCE\n66: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n67: skill_reference:\n68:   skill: system-deep-loop\n69:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md\n70:   references:\n71:     loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n72:     spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\n73:     state_format: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\n74:     convergence: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n75:   templates:\n76:     config: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n77:     strategy: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n78: \n79: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n80: # AGENT CONFIGURATION\n81: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n82: agent_config:\n83:   agent: deep-research\n84:   agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n85:   # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n86:   model: opus\n87:   leaf_only: true\n88:   tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n89:   mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n90:   tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n91: \n92: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n93: # STATE FILE PATHS\n94: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n95: state_paths:\n96:   # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n97:   # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n98:   # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n99:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n100:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n101:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n102:   status_ledger: \"{artifact_dir}/orchestration-status.log\"\n103:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n104:   registry: \"{artifact_dir}/findings-registry.json\"\n105:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n106:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n107:   run_now_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-run-now\"\n108:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n109:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n110:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n111:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n112:   # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n113:   # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n114:   # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n115:   # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n116:   # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n117:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n118:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n119:   research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n120:   resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n121:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n122:   synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n123: \n124: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n125: # WORKFLOW\n126: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n127: workflow:\n128: \n129:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n130:     description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n131:     note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n132:     branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n133:     if_present:\n134:       bind:\n135:         artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n136:         artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n137:         artifact_subfolder: null\n138:         artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n139:     if_absent:\n140:       command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n141:       outputs:\n142:         - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n143:         - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n144:         - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n145:         - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n146: \n147:   step_fanout_spawn:\n148:     description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n149:     skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n150:     instructions: |\n151:       Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n152:       isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n153:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n154:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n155:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n156:     sub_steps:\n157:       step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n158:         description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n159:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n160:         command: |\n161:           node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n162:             --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n163:             --loop-type research \\\n164:             --research-topic \"{research_topic}\" \\\n165:             --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n166:             --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n167:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n168:         wait_for_completion: true\n169:       step_fanout_spawn_native:\n170:         description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-research sub-agent\"\n171:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n172:         for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n173:         dispatch:\n174:           agent: deep-research\n175:           model: opus\n176:           context: |\n177:             Execute the deep-research loop with these parameters:\n178:               spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n179:               config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n180:               session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n181:               executor: native\n182:             Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n183:         wait_for_completion: true\n184: \n185:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n186:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n187:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n188:   phase_init:\n189:     purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n190:     steps:\n191: \n192:       step_preflight_contract:\n193:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n194:         verify:\n195:           - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold, convergence_mode]\n196:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n197:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n198:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n199:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n200: \n201:       step_create_directories:\n202:         action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n203:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n204: \n205:       step_detect_resource_map:\n206:         action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n207:         inspect:\n208:           - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n209:         classify:\n210:           present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n211:           absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n212:         outputs:\n213:           - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n214:           - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n215: \n216:       step_resolve_canonical_names:\n217:         action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n218:         inspect_legacy:\n219:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n220:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n221:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n222:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n223:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n224:         migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n225:         on_legacy_read:\n226:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n227: \n228:       step_acquire_lock:\n229:         action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n230:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n231:         on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n232:         note: \"Uses the promoted runtime/ loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n233:         # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n234:         # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n235:         on_halt:\n236:           action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n237:           applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n238:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n239:         on_cancel:\n240:           action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n241:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n242:         on_workflow_exit:\n243:           action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n244:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n245: \n246:       step_classify_session:\n247:         action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n248:         inspect:\n249:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n250:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n251:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n252:         classify:\n253:           fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n254:           resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder; missing wait-checkpoint fields are read as nextRunAt:null and remainingDelayMs:null\"\n255:           completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n256:           invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n257:         outputs:\n258:           - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n259:         on_resume:\n260:           # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n261:           # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n262:           gate3_classification: write-path\n263:           gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n264:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n265:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n266:           skip_to: phase_loop\n267:         on_restart:\n268:           action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n269:           command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n270:           set:\n271:             lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n272:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n273:             generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n274:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n275:           skip_to: step_create_config\n276:         note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n277:         on_completed_session:\n278:           log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n279:           halt: true\n280:           message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n281:         on_invalid_state:\n282:           halt: true\n283:           message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n284:         on_fresh:\n285:           action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n286: \n287:       step_resolve_session_id:\n288:         action: \"Resolve init session id from caller when supplied, else preserve the auto-generated fallback\"\n289:         branch_on: \"session_id\"\n290:         if_present:\n291:           bind:\n292:             session_id_init: \"{session_id}\"\n293:         if_absent:\n294:           bind:\n295:             session_id_init: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n296: \n297:       step_create_config:\n298:         action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n299:         template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n300:         populate:\n301:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n302:           maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n303:           minIterations: 3\n304:           # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n305:           convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n306:           antiConvergence.convergenceMode: \"{convergence_mode}\"\n307:           antiConvergence.divergent: {}\n308:           stuckThreshold: 3\n309:           minIdeaObservations: 2\n310:           maxDurationMinutes: 120\n311:           specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n312:           resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n313:           # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n314:           # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n315:           resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n316:           createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n317:           status: \"initialized\"\n318:           executionMode: \"auto\"\n319:           lineage.sessionId: \"{session_id_init}\"\n320:           lineage.parentSessionId: null\n321:           lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n322:           lineage.generation: 1\n323:           lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n324:           nextRunAt: null\n325:           remainingDelayMs: null\n326:         output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n327: \n328:       step_create_state_log:\n329:         action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n330:         # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n331:         content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"antiConvergence\":{\"convergenceMode\":\"{convergence_mode}\",\"divergent\":{}},\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\",\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}'\n332:         output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n333: \n334:       step_create_strategy:\n335:         action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n336:         template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n337:         populate:\n338:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n339:           key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n340:           known_context: \"None\"\n341:           known_context_summary: \"None\"\n342:           max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n343:           convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n344:         output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n345: \n346:       step_create_registry:\n347:         action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n348:         content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n349:         output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n350: \n351:       step_enrich_strategy_context:\n352:         action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n353:         condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n354:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n355:         note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n356: \n357:       step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n358:         action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n359:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n360:         note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n361: \n362:       step_detect_spec_present:\n363:         action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n364:         inspect:\n365:           - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n366:           - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n367:         classify:\n368:           no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n369:           spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n370:           spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n371:           conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n372:         outputs:\n373:           - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n374:           - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n375:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n376: \n377:       step_preinit_spec_branch:\n378:         action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n379:         protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"\n380:         branches:\n381:           no-spec:\n382:             create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n383:             seed_markers:\n384:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n385:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n386:             requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n387:             scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n388:             set:\n389:               folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n390:               validate_spec_doc: true\n391:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n392:           spec-present:\n393:             edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n394:             set:\n395:               validate_spec_doc: true\n396:             idempotency_check:\n397:               host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n398:               normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n399:               if_match:\n400:                 skip_append: true\n401:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n402:               if_no_match:\n403:                 append_only:\n404:                   - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n405:                     content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n406:                   - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n407:                     content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n408:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n409:           spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n410:             verify_markers:\n411:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n412:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n413:             set:\n414:               validate_spec_doc: false\n415:             note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n416:           conflict-detected:\n417:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n418:             halt: true\n419: \n420:       step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n421:         action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n422:         condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n423:         command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n424:         note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n425: \n426:       step_telemetry_heartbeat_started:\n427:         action: \"Emit a single-loop started row in the orchestration status ledger\"\n428:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n429:         canonical_lifecycle_event: \"iteration_start\"\n430:         command: |\n431:           node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n432:           import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n433: \n434:           import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n435:           import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n436: \n437:           const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n438:           const config = JSON.parse(readFileSync('{state_paths.config}', 'utf8'));\n439:           const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n440:           const sessionId = String(config.lineage?.sessionId ?? '{AUTO_SESSION_ID}');\n441:           const generation = Number(config.lineage?.generation ?? 1);\n442:           const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n443:           const row = {\n444:             event: 'started',\n445:             label: 'single',\n446:             at: timestamp,\n447:             duration_ms: 0,\n448:             loop_type: 'research',\n449:             sessionId,\n450:             generation,\n451:             gauges: { iterations: 0, elapsed_ms: 0, score: 0 },\n452:           };\n453: \n454:           const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n455:             diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, gauges: { iterations: 0, score: 0 } },\n456:             diffField: 'state_hash',\n457:           });\n458:           if (appended) {\n459:             try {\n460:               appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n461:                 producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n462:                 stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n463:                 subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation },\n464:                 event: row.event,\n465:                 status: 'running',\n466:               });\n467:             } catch {}\n468:           }\n469:           EOF\n470:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n471:         outputs:\n472:           - status_ledger_started: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event started\"\n473: \n474:       step_init_complete:\n475:         log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created.\"\n476:         set: { current_iteration: 1, current_segment: 1, stuck_count: 0 }\n477: \n478:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n479:   # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n480:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n481:   phase_loop:\n482:     purpose: Dispatch agent iterations until convergence\n483:     repeat: true\n484:     max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n485:     steps:\n486: \n487:       step_read_state:\n488:         action: \"Read current state from JSONL and strategy\"\n489:         read:\n490:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n491:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n492:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n493:         extract:\n494:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n495:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n496:           - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n497:           - last_newInfoRatio: \"Extract newInfoRatio from last iteration record\"\n498:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n499:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n500:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n\n(Showing lines 1-500 of 1946. Use offset=501 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","text":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\naction: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_research_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n  approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n  mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nuser_inputs:\n  research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n  max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n  convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n  convergence_mode: \"[default|off|sliding-window|divergent] - Convergence policy modifier. Default: default.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# CONTEXT LOADING\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n  behavior:\n    if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n    if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# SKILL REFERENCE\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nskill_reference:\n  skill: system-deep-loop\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/SKILL.md\n  references:\n    loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n    spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\n    state_format: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\n    convergence: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n  templates:\n    config: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n    strategy: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# AGENT CONFIGURATION\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nagent_config:\n  agent: deep-research\n  agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n  # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n  model: opus\n  leaf_only: true\n  tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n  mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n  tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# STATE FILE PATHS\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nstate_paths:\n  # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n  # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n  # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n  packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n  config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n  state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n  status_ledger: \"{artifact_dir}/orchestration-status.log\"\n  strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n  registry: \"{artifact_dir}/findings-registry.json\"\n  dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n  pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n  run_now_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-run-now\"\n  lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n  iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n  iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n  # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n  # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n  # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n  # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n  # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n  delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n  delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n  research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n  resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n  synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# WORKFLOW\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n    branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n    if_present:\n      bind:\n        artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_subfolder: null\n        artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n    if_absent:\n      command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n      outputs:\n        - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n        - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n        - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n        - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n\n  step_fanout_spawn:\n    description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n    skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n    instructions: |\n      Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n      isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n      After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n      phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n      phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n    sub_steps:\n      step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n        description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n            --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n            --loop-type research \\\n            --research-topic \"{research_topic}\" \\\n            --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n            --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n      step_fanout_spawn_native:\n        description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-research sub-agent\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n        for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n        dispatch:\n          agent: deep-research\n          model: opus\n          context: |\n            Execute the deep-research loop with these parameters:\n              spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n              config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n              session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n              executor: native\n            Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold, convergence_mode]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n\n      step_detect_resource_map:\n        action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n        classify:\n          present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n          absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n        outputs:\n          - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n          - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_resolve_canonical_names:\n        action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n        inspect_legacy:\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n        migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n        on_legacy_read:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n        note: \"Uses the promoted runtime/ loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n        on_workflow_exit:\n          action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n\n      step_classify_session:\n        action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        classify:\n          fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n          resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder; missing wait-checkpoint fields are read as nextRunAt:null and remainingDelayMs:null\"\n          completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n          invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n        on_resume:\n          # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n          # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n          gate3_classification: write-path\n          gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n        on_invalid_state:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n        on_fresh:\n          action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n\n      step_resolve_session_id:\n        action: \"Resolve init session id from caller when supplied, else preserve the auto-generated fallback\"\n        branch_on: \"session_id\"\n        if_present:\n          bind:\n            session_id_init: \"{session_id}\"\n        if_absent:\n          bind:\n            session_id_init: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n\n      step_create_config:\n        action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          minIterations: 3\n          # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n          convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          antiConvergence.convergenceMode: \"{convergence_mode}\"\n          antiConvergence.divergent: {}\n          stuckThreshold: 3\n          minIdeaObservations: 2\n          maxDurationMinutes: 120\n          specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n          resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n          # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n          # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n          resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n          createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          status: \"initialized\"\n          executionMode: \"auto\"\n          lineage.sessionId: \"{session_id_init}\"\n          lineage.parentSessionId: null\n          lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n          lineage.generation: 1\n          lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n          nextRunAt: null\n          remainingDelayMs: null\n        output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n\n      step_create_state_log:\n        action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n        # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n        content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"antiConvergence\":{\"convergenceMode\":\"{convergence_mode}\",\"divergent\":{}},\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\",\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n\n      step_create_strategy:\n        action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n          known_context: \"None\"\n          known_context_summary: \"None\"\n          max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_create_registry:\n        action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n        content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_context:\n        action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n        condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n        action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_detect_spec_present:\n        action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n        classify:\n          no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n          spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n          conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n        outputs:\n          - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n          - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_preinit_spec_branch:\n        action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n        protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"\n        branches:\n          no-spec:\n            create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            seed_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n            scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n            set:\n              folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-present:\n            edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            idempotency_check:\n              host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n              normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n              if_match:\n                skip_append: true\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n              if_no_match:\n                append_only:\n                  - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n                    content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n                  - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n                    content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n            verify_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: false\n            note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n          conflict-detected:\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n            halt: true\n\n      step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n        action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n        condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n        command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n        note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n\n      step_telemetry_heartbeat_started:\n        action: \"Emit a single-loop started row in the orchestration status ledger\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n        canonical_lifecycle_event: \"iteration_start\"\n        command: |\n          node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n          import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n          import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n          import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n\n          const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n          const config = JSON.parse(readFileSync('{state_paths.config}', 'utf8'));\n          const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n          const sessionId = String(config.lineage?.sessionId ?? '{AUTO_SESSION_ID}');\n          const generation = Number(config.lineage?.generation ?? 1);\n          const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n          const row = {\n            event: 'started',\n            label: 'single',\n            at: timestamp,\n            duration_ms: 0,\n            loop_type: 'research',\n            sessionId,\n            generation,\n            gauges: { iterations: 0, elapsed_ms: 0, score: 0 },\n          };\n\n          const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n            diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, gauges: { iterations: 0, score: 0 } },\n            diffField: 'state_hash',\n          });\n          if (appended) {\n            try {\n              appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n                producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n                stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n                subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation },\n                event: row.event,\n                status: 'running',\n              });\n            } catch {}\n          }\n          EOF\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        outputs:\n          - status_ledger_started: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event started\"\n\n      step_init_complete:\n        log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created.\"\n        set: { current_iteration: 1, current_segment: 1, stuck_count: 0 }\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_loop:\n    purpose: Dispatch agent iterations until convergence\n    repeat: true\n    max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n    steps:\n\n      step_read_state:\n        action: \"Read current state from JSONL and strategy\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n          - last_newInfoRatio: \"Extract newInfoRatio from last iteration record\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":500,"totalLines":1946,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1783744105832,"end":1783744105841}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0790739cab9e452d016a51c669b8088191a6a5d953937fb15d"}},"id":"prt_f4f6f0d67001k8LLM0JvyV2L8v","sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","messageID":"msg_f4f6ee7b10016C2h7m6rTvUsO4"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783744105852,"sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_8KO3HmMFT9TrBCZtZuIvRYnU","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"deep_research_auto|phase_init|phase_main_loop|phase_synthesis|workflow.*yaml|execute.*yaml","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop","include":"*.{cjs,ts,md}"},"output":"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/changelog/v1.11.0.0.md:\n  Line 46: | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` | `step_marker_scan` added (H-2 enforcement). Touched in 74782acfb. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/changelog/v1.10.0.0.md:\n  Line 121: | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml`               | Pre-dispatch audit for non-native. Copilot size check with @path fallback.                                                                                |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:\n  Line 16: - Both `deep_research_auto.yaml` and `deep_research_confirm.yaml` now call `deep_loop_graph_upsert` after `step_reduce_state` (persisting iteration `graphEvents` to the SQLite store) and `deep_loop_graph_convergence` before the inline 3-signal vote in `step_check_convergence`. The combined stop rule: STOP requires BOTH the inline vote and graph decision to agree; `STOP_BLOCKED` routes to the `blocked_stop` emission path.\n\n  Line 69: | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml`                                           | Modified | Wired step_emit_blocked_stop + step_normalize_pause_events + graph upsert + graph convergence |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/ME