{"type":"text","timestamp":1783744353325,"sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","part":{"id":"prt_f4f72b99d001tyEt4dgjektVYD","messageID":"msg_f4f72a93e001mdLmoi3O25kOaA","sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","type":"text","text":"Iteration 1 established the current coverage boundary and eliminated two overlapping directions. Before the next pass, I’m mechanically verifying the three required artifacts, then refreshing lineage-local strategy, registry, and dashboard state without calling the reducer’s spec-root resolver, which does not accept the fan-out override.","time":{"start":1783744346525,"end":1783744353324},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0029b60fde6fff30016a51c75a81fc8191b7fafbedb6d29cdb","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783744353408,"sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_PxBtggx8ydnBpjFYkrboVIuK","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"node \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs\" --loop-type research --artifact-dir \".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol\" --iteration 1 --json","timeout":120000,"workdir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public"},"output":"{\"ok\":true,\"reason\":null,\"detail\":\"iteration 1 complete: narrative + route-proof + delta\"}\n","metadata":{"output":"{\"ok\":true,\"reason\":null,\"detail\":\"iteration 1 complete: narrative + route-proof + delta\"}\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"node \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs\" --loop-type research --artifact-dir \".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol\" --iteration 1 --json","time":{"start":1783744353406,"end":1783744353408}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0029b60fde6fff30016a51c76149a88191a1bb5286ada46a85"}},"id":"prt_f4f72d42e001dqukbSJjn7SvEN","sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","messageID":"msg_f4f72a93e001mdLmoi3O25kOaA"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783744353417,"sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_a6JvfqTLFoZ1HUcNkivBMxw9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-state.jsonl","offset":1,"limit":20},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-state.jsonl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"What additional OpenCode plugins and Claude hooks could we build based on existing repo skills? Ground every candidate in a real skill under .opencode/skills/ and name its concrete runtime surface (OpenCode plugin hook: tool.execute.before/after, session.*, experimental.*; or Claude hook: PreToolUse/PostToolUse/SessionStart/UserPromptSubmit/Stop/SessionEnd).\",\"maxIterations\":5,\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"antiConvergence\":{\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"stopPolicy\":\"convergence\"},\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-07-11T04:29:38Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities\",\"artifactDir\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gptsol-1783743995827-g7k8yl\",\"generation\":1,\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}\n2: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":1,\"run\":1,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"newInfoRatio\":1.0,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Skill and runtime inventory\",\"findingsCount\":7,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Seven distinct current-state findings established the baseline inventory, ownership boundaries, and four high-value automation families with no prior iteration evidence.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Which skill contracts are plausible automation candidates?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Which skill contracts are plausible automation candidates?\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"generic prompt-context plugin\",\"hook-owned deep-loop convergence\"],\"toolsUsed\":[\"Glob\",\"Grep\",\"Read\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\".opencode/plugins/README.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/sk-git/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-11T04:34:00Z\",\"durationMs\":264000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gptsol-1783743995827-g7k8yl\",\"generation\":1,\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast\",\"reasoningEffort\":null,\"serviceTier\":null}}\n\n(End of file - total 2 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"What additional OpenCode plugins and Claude hooks could we build based on existing repo skills? Ground every candidate in a real skill under .opencode/skills/ and name its concrete runtime surface (OpenCode plugin hook: tool.execute.before/after, session.*, experimental.*; or Claude hook: PreToolUse/PostToolUse/SessionStart/UserPromptSubmit/Stop/SessionEnd).\",\"maxIterations\":5,\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"antiConvergence\":{\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"stopPolicy\":\"convergence\"},\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-07-11T04:29:38Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities\",\"artifactDir\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gptsol-1783743995827-g7k8yl\",\"generation\":1,\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":1,\"run\":1,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"newInfoRatio\":1.0,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Skill and runtime inventory\",\"findingsCount\":7,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Seven distinct current-state findings established the baseline inventory, ownership boundaries, and four high-value automation families with no prior iteration evidence.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Which skill contracts are plausible automation candidates?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Which skill contracts are plausible automation candidates?\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"generic prompt-context plugin\",\"hook-owned deep-loop convergence\"],\"toolsUsed\":[\"Glob\",\"Grep\",\"Read\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\".opencode/plugins/README.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/sk-git/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-11T04:34:00Z\",\"durationMs\":264000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gptsol-1783743995827-g7k8yl\",\"generation\":1,\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast\",\"reasoningEffort\":null,\"serviceTier\":null}}","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-state.jsonl","text":"{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"What additional OpenCode plugins and Claude hooks could we build based on existing repo skills? Ground every candidate in a real skill under .opencode/skills/ and name its concrete runtime surface (OpenCode plugin hook: tool.execute.before/after, session.*, experimental.*; or Claude hook: PreToolUse/PostToolUse/SessionStart/UserPromptSubmit/Stop/SessionEnd).\",\"maxIterations\":5,\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"antiConvergence\":{\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"stopPolicy\":\"convergence\"},\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-07-11T04:29:38Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities\",\"artifactDir\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gptsol-1783743995827-g7k8yl\",\"generation\":1,\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":1,\"run\":1,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"newInfoRatio\":1.0,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Skill and runtime inventory\",\"findingsCount\":7,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Seven distinct current-state findings established the baseline inventory, ownership boundaries, and four high-value automation families with no prior iteration evidence.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Which skill contracts are plausible automation candidates?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Which skill contracts are plausible automation candidates?\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"generic prompt-context plugin\",\"hook-owned deep-loop convergence\"],\"toolsUsed\":[\"Glob\",\"Grep\",\"Read\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\".opencode/plugins/README.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/sk-git/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-11T04:34:00Z\",\"durationMs\":264000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gptsol-1783743995827-g7k8yl\",\"generation\":1,\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast\",\"reasoningEffort\":null,\"serviceTier\":null}}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":2,"totalLines":2,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-state.jsonl","time":{"start":1783744353410,"end":1783744353415}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0029b60fde6fff30016a51c76149bc8191bed806ad7d37fc51"}},"id":"prt_f4f72d47f001AUww5zTWB02qDW","sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","messageID":"msg_f4f72a93e001mdLmoi3O25kOaA"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783744353417,"sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_QbMhqwitY5gBM7Jt31dHTgTN","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/iterations/iteration-001.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/iterations/iteration-001.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Iteration 1: Skill and Runtime Inventory\n2: \n3: ## Focus\n4: \n5: Inventory the current OpenCode plugin surface and identify skill contracts whose repeated enforcement or routing logic is a plausible hook candidate.\n6: \n7: ## Actions Taken\n8: \n9: 1. Enumerated all `.opencode/skills/**/SKILL.md` packets.\n10: 2. Enumerated current OpenCode plugin entrypoints and tests.\n11: 3. Searched the repository for supported OpenCode and Claude hook names.\n12: 4. Read the plugin entrypoint contract and representative governance, quality, git, advisor, and deep-loop skills.\n13: \n14: ## Findings\n15: \n16: 1. The plugin layer already establishes a reusable architecture: minimal default-export-only entrypoints in `.opencode/plugins/`, with bridge and schema logic owned by the source skill. New candidates should follow that ownership split rather than placing helper modules in the auto-load directory. [SOURCE: .opencode/plugins/README.md:24-38] [SOURCE: .opencode/plugins/README.md:56-67]\n17: 2. Existing plugins cover prompt-time skill advice, code-graph context, memory continuity, goal state, deep-loop dispatch guards, dist freshness, and session cleanup. The most valuable net-new candidates therefore sit at other workflow boundaries: mutation intake, destructive command execution, post-edit quality checks, and stop-time completion evidence. [SOURCE: .opencode/plugins/README.md:42-52]\n18: 3. `system-spec-kit` contains a high-frequency manual mutation gate: all file modifications require spec-folder documentation, while read-only work and explicit skip are exceptions. This is a strong candidate for prompt-time classification and pre-mutation enforcement rather than another general context injector. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md:28-61]\n19: 4. `code-quality` defines deterministic post-write checks by target path, including comment hygiene, dist staleness, and OpenCode-specific authoring checklists. It already has a Claude `PostToolUse` warning hook for comment hygiene, making a broader cross-runtime post-edit quality router a natural extension. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/SKILL.md:54-110] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/SKILL.md:124-136]\n20: 5. `sk-git` contains safety rules that are mechanically recognizable before shell execution: no direct branch creation, no force-push to main/master, scoped staging, and deterministic commit-message structure. These rules are suitable for command interception because they do not require broad semantic judgment in their blocking core. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-git/SKILL.md:291-317] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-git/SKILL.md:459-469]\n21: 6. `system-skill-advisor` already owns prompt-time recommendation and skill graph freshness. New routing hooks should consume this service or validate its result, not duplicate scorer logic. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:39-85] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:116-159]\n22: 7. `system-deep-loop` centralizes mode resolution through `mode-registry.json` and forbids flattening mode-specific lifecycle logic into the hub. Hook candidates around deep loops should enforce route and lifecycle boundaries, not attempt to run convergence or synthesis themselves. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:35-70] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:93-110]\n23: \n24: ## Questions Answered\n25: \n26: - Which existing skills contain repeatable enforcement, routing, recovery, or quality logic that is currently manual or prompt-dependent?\n27: \n28: ## Questions Remaining\n29: \n30: - Which exact OpenCode surfaces best fit the candidate contracts?\n31: - Which exact Claude surfaces best fit the candidate contracts?\n32: - How should candidates be prioritized?\n33: - Which ideas should be eliminated due to overlap or unsuitable runtime semantics?\n34: \n35: ## Ruled Out\n36: \n37: - A new generic prompt-context plugin: existing skill-advisor, memory, code-graph, and goal plugins already occupy that layer; another broad injector would add token cost and precedence ambiguity. [SOURCE: .opencode/plugins/README.md:42-52]\n38: - Embedding deep-loop convergence in a hook: the mode packets and runtime own convergence; the hub explicitly must remain routing-only. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:88-110]\n39: \n40: ## Dead Ends\n41: \n42: - Broad repository hook-name search produced many generated and archived references; direct plugin README and skill contracts were more reliable for current-state inventory.\n43: \n44: ## Edge Cases\n45: \n46: - Ambiguous input: \"additional\" was interpreted as net-new behavior not already supplied by the seven current plugin entrypoints.\n47: - Contradictory evidence: none.\n48: - Missing dependencies: memory context timed out; direct repository sources replaced it.\n49: - Partial success: candidate families are identified, but exact surface mapping remains for later iterations.\n50: \n51: ## Sources Consulted\n52: \n53: - `.opencode/plugins/README.md:24-67`\n54: - `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md:28-61`\n55: - `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/SKILL.md:54-136`\n56: - `.opencode/skills/sk-git/SKILL.md:291-317,459-469`\n57: - `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:39-159`\n58: - `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:35-110`\n59: \n60: ## Assessment\n61: \n62: - New information ratio: 1.0\n63: - Novelty justification: Seven distinct current-state findings established the baseline inventory, ownership boundaries, and four high-value automation families with no prior iteration evidence.\n64: - Questions addressed: skill candidates and existing overlap.\n65: - Questions answered: skill contracts suitable for hook automation.\n66: \n67: ## Reflection\n68: \n69: - What worked and why: reading current plugin documentation alongside source-skill contracts separated genuine gaps from already-shipped behavior.\n70: - What did not work and why: broad hook-term search was noisy because it included generated and archived material.\n71: - What I would do differently: narrow the next pass to current plugin implementations and exact supported hook keys.\n72: \n73: ## Recommended Next Focus\n74: \n75: Map concrete OpenCode plugin candidates to `tool.execute.before/after`, `session.*`, or `experimental.*`, validating feasibility and overlap against current entrypoints.\n\n(End of file - total 75 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Iteration 1: Skill and Runtime Inventory\n\n## Focus\n\nInventory the current OpenCode plugin surface and identify skill contracts whose repeated enforcement or routing logic is a plausible hook candidate.\n\n## Actions Taken\n\n1. Enumerated all `.opencode/skills/**/SKILL.md` packets.\n2. Enumerated current OpenCode plugin entrypoints and tests.\n3. Searched the repository for supported OpenCode and Claude hook names.\n4. Read the plugin entrypoint contract and representative governance, quality, git, advisor, and deep-loop skills.\n\n## Findings\n\n1. The plugin layer already establishes a reusable architecture: minimal default-export-only entrypoints in `.opencode/plugins/`, with bridge and schema logic owned by the source skill. New candidates should follow that ownership split rather than placing helper modules in the auto-load directory. [SOURCE: .opencode/plugins/README.md:24-38] [SOURCE: .opencode/plugins/README.md:56-67]\n2. Existing plugins cover prompt-time skill advice, code-graph context, memory continuity, goal state, deep-loop dispatch guards, dist freshness, and session cleanup. The most valuable net-new candidates therefore sit at other workflow boundaries: mutation intake, destructive command execution, post-edit quality checks, and stop-time completion evidence. [SOURCE: .opencode/plugins/README.md:42-52]\n3. `system-spec-kit` contains a high-frequency manual mutation gate: all file modifications require spec-folder documentation, while read-only work and explicit skip are exceptions. This is a strong candidate for prompt-time classification and pre-mutation enforcement rather than another general context injector. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md:28-61]\n4. `code-quality` defines deterministic post-write checks by target path, including comment hygiene, dist staleness, and OpenCode-specific authoring checklists. It already has a Claude `PostToolUse` warning hook for comment hygiene, making a broader cross-runtime post-edit quality router a natural extension. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/SKILL.md:54-110] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/SKILL.md:124-136]\n5. `sk-git` contains safety rules that are mechanically recognizable before shell execution: no direct branch creation, no force-push to main/master, scoped staging, and deterministic commit-message structure. These rules are suitable for command interception because they do not require broad semantic judgment in their blocking core. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-git/SKILL.md:291-317] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-git/SKILL.md:459-469]","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/iterations/iteration-001.md","text":"# Iteration 1: Skill and Runtime Inventory\n\n## Focus\n\nInventory the current OpenCode plugin surface and identify skill contracts whose repeated enforcement or routing logic is a plausible hook candidate.\n\n## Actions Taken\n\n1. Enumerated all `.opencode/skills/**/SKILL.md` packets.\n2. Enumerated current OpenCode plugin entrypoints and tests.\n3. Searched the repository for supported OpenCode and Claude hook names.\n4. Read the plugin entrypoint contract and representative governance, quality, git, advisor, and deep-loop skills.\n\n## Findings\n\n1. The plugin layer already establishes a reusable architecture: minimal default-export-only entrypoints in `.opencode/plugins/`, with bridge and schema logic owned by the source skill. New candidates should follow that ownership split rather than placing helper modules in the auto-load directory. [SOURCE: .opencode/plugins/README.md:24-38] [SOURCE: .opencode/plugins/README.md:56-67]\n2. Existing plugins cover prompt-time skill advice, code-graph context, memory continuity, goal state, deep-loop dispatch guards, dist freshness, and session cleanup. The most valuable net-new candidates therefore sit at other workflow boundaries: mutation intake, destructive command execution, post-edit quality checks, and stop-time completion evidence. [SOURCE: .opencode/plugins/README.md:42-52]\n3. `system-spec-kit` contains a high-frequency manual mutation gate: all file modifications require spec-folder documentation, while read-only work and explicit skip are exceptions. This is a strong candidate for prompt-time classification and pre-mutation enforcement rather than another general context injector. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md:28-61]\n4. `code-quality` defines deterministic post-write checks by target path, including comment hygiene, dist staleness, and OpenCode-specific authoring checklists. It already has a Claude `PostToolUse` warning hook for comment hygiene, making a broader cross-runtime post-edit quality router a natural extension. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/SKILL.md:54-110] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/SKILL.md:124-136]\n5. `sk-git` contains safety rules that are mechanically recognizable before shell execution: no direct branch creation, no force-push to main/master, scoped staging, and deterministic commit-message structure. These rules are suitable for command interception because they do not require broad semantic judgment in their blocking core. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-git/SKILL.md:291-317] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-git/SKILL.md:459-469]\n6. `system-skill-advisor` already owns prompt-time recommendation and skill graph freshness. New routing hooks should consume this service or validate its result, not duplicate scorer logic. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:39-85] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:116-159]\n7. `system-deep-loop` centralizes mode resolution through `mode-registry.json` and forbids flattening mode-specific lifecycle logic into the hub. Hook candidates around deep loops should enforce route and lifecycle boundaries, not attempt to run convergence or synthesis themselves. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:35-70] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:93-110]\n\n## Questions Answered\n\n- Which existing skills contain repeatable enforcement, routing, recovery, or quality logic that is currently manual or prompt-dependent?\n\n## Questions Remaining\n\n- Which exact OpenCode surfaces best fit the candidate contracts?\n- Which exact Claude surfaces best fit the candidate contracts?\n- How should candidates be prioritized?\n- Which ideas should be eliminated due to overlap or unsuitable runtime semantics?\n\n## Ruled Out\n\n- A new generic prompt-context plugin: existing skill-advisor, memory, code-graph, and goal plugins already occupy that layer; another broad injector would add token cost and precedence ambiguity. [SOURCE: .opencode/plugins/README.md:42-52]\n- Embedding deep-loop convergence in a hook: the mode packets and runtime own convergence; the hub explicitly must remain routing-only. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:88-110]\n\n## Dead Ends\n\n- Broad repository hook-name search produced many generated and archived references; direct plugin README and skill contracts were more reliable for current-state inventory.\n\n## Edge Cases\n\n- Ambiguous input: \"additional\" was interpreted as net-new behavior not already supplied by the seven current plugin entrypoints.\n- Contradictory evidence: none.\n- Missing dependencies: memory context timed out; direct repository sources replaced it.\n- Partial success: candidate families are identified, but exact surface mapping remains for later iterations.\n\n## Sources Consulted\n\n- `.opencode/plugins/README.md:24-67`\n- `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md:28-61`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/SKILL.md:54-136`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-git/SKILL.md:291-317,459-469`\n- `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:39-159`\n- `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/SKILL.md:35-110`\n\n## Assessment\n\n- New information ratio: 1.0\n- Novelty justification: Seven distinct current-state findings established the baseline inventory, ownership boundaries, and four high-value automation families with no prior iteration evidence.\n- Questions addressed: skill candidates and existing overlap.\n- Questions answered: skill contracts suitable for hook automation.\n\n## Reflection\n\n- What worked and why: reading current plugin documentation alongside source-skill contracts separated genuine gaps from already-shipped behavior.\n- What did not work and why: broad hook-term search was noisy because it included generated and archived material.\n- What I would do differently: narrow the next pass to current plugin implementations and exact supported hook keys.\n\n## Recommended Next Focus\n\nMap concrete OpenCode plugin candidates to `tool.execute.before/after`, `session.*`, or `experimental.*`, validating feasibility and overlap against current entrypoints.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":75,"totalLines":75,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/iterations/iteration-001.md","time":{"start":1783744353412,"end":1783744353416}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0029b60fde6fff30016a51c76149c481918d937785df7c8635"}},"id":"prt_f4f72d483001Fyx5ph1qRkNIcX","sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","messageID":"msg_f4f72a93e001mdLmoi3O25kOaA"}}
