{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783744396234,"sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_USrDdIyV23CXqooRvgfFuix9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy: Plugin and Hook Opportunities\n2: \n3: ## 2. TOPIC\n4: \n5: Identify additional OpenCode plugins and Claude hooks grounded in existing `.opencode/skills/` contracts, and map every candidate to a concrete supported runtime hook surface.\n6: \n7: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n8: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n9: \n10: - [x] Which existing skills contain repeatable enforcement, routing, recovery, or quality logic that is currently manual or prompt-dependent?\n11: - [ ] Which additional OpenCode plugins are justified, and which exact `tool.execute.before/after`, `session.*`, or `experimental.*` surfaces should host them?\n12: - [ ] Which additional Claude hooks are justified, and which exact `PreToolUse`, `PostToolUse`, `SessionStart`, `UserPromptSubmit`, `Stop`, or `SessionEnd` surfaces should host them?\n13: - [ ] How should candidates be prioritized by value, feasibility, overlap, false-positive risk, and blast radius?\n14: - [ ] Which attractive ideas should be ruled out because the runtime surface is unsuitable or existing infrastructure already owns the behavior?\n15: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n16: \n17: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n18: \n19: - Do not implement plugins or hooks.\n20: - Do not propose candidates without a real skill source and concrete runtime surface.\n21: - Do not treat undocumented runtime events as available.\n22: - Do not modify files outside this detached lineage directory.\n23: \n24: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n25: \n26: - At least three evidence iterations have completed.\n27: - Every candidate is grounded in a cited skill and mapped to an allowed runtime surface.\n28: - OpenCode and Claude opportunities, prioritization, and eliminated alternatives are covered.\n29: - Convergence is legal under the configured policy, or five iterations have completed.\n30: \n31: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n32: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n33: \n34: - Which skill contracts are plausible automation candidates? Candidate families are mutation intake (`system-spec-kit`), destructive command safety (`sk-git`), post-edit quality (`code-quality`), and route/lifecycle validation (`system-skill-advisor`, `system-deep-loop`).\n35: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n36: \n37: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n38: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n39: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n40: \n41: - Current plugin inventory plus source-skill contract reads efficiently separated gaps from already-shipped behavior. (iteration 1)\n42: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n43: \n44: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n45: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n46: \n47: - The initial memory-context lookup timed out; repository evidence is the fallback.\n48: - Broad hook-term search was noisy because generated and archived artifacts dominated results. (iteration 1)\n49: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n50: \n51: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n52: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n53: \n54: - Generic prompt-context plugin: overlaps advisor, memory, code-graph, and goal entrypoints. (iteration 1)\n55: - Hook-owned deep-loop convergence: violates mode-packet and runtime ownership. (iteration 1)\n56: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n57: \n58: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n59: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n60: \n61: None yet.\n62: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n63: \n64: <!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n65: ## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n66: \n67: - Completed pivots: 0\n68: - Failed pivots: 0\n69: - Saturated: none yet\n70: - Remaining frontier: exact OpenCode mapping, Claude mapping, prioritization, and risk controls\n71: <!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n72: \n73: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n74: ## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n75: \n76: - Which OpenCode surface best fits each candidate while preserving current plugin ownership?\n77: - Which Claude surface provides equivalent timing without pretending runtime parity?\n78: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n79: \n80: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n81: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n82: \n83: Map concrete OpenCode plugin candidates to `tool.execute.before/after`, `session.*`, or `experimental.*`, validating feasibility and overlap against current entrypoints.\n84: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n85: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n86: \n87: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n88: \n89: - The requested runtime surface set is closed: OpenCode `tool.execute.before/after`, `session.*`, `experimental.*`; Claude `PreToolUse`, `PostToolUse`, `SessionStart`, `UserPromptSubmit`, `Stop`, `SessionEnd`.\n90: - Every candidate must cite a real skill under `.opencode/skills/`.\n91: - Memory context was unavailable after timeout; direct repository evidence is authoritative for this lineage.\n92: \n93: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n94: \n95: - Max iterations: 5\n96: - Minimum iterations: 3\n97: - Convergence threshold: 0.05\n98: - Stop policy: convergence\n99: - Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n100: - Allowed write root: `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol`\n101: - Executor: `cli-opencode`, model `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast`\n102: - Session: `fanout-gptsol-1783743995827-g7k8yl`\n\n(End of file - total 102 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy: Plugin and Hook Opportunities\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n\nIdentify additional OpenCode plugins and Claude hooks grounded in existing `.opencode/skills/` contracts, and map every candidate to a concrete supported runtime hook surface.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n\n- [x] Which existing skills contain repeatable enforcement, routing, recovery, or quality logic that is currently manual or prompt-dependent?\n- [ ] Which additional OpenCode plugins are justified, and which exact `tool.execute.before/after`, `session.*`, or `experimental.*` surfaces should host them?\n- [ ] Which additional Claude hooks are justified, and which exact `PreToolUse`, `PostToolUse`, `SessionStart`, `UserPromptSubmit`, `Stop`, or `SessionEnd` surfaces should host them?\n- [ ] How should candidates be prioritized by value, feasibility, overlap, false-positive risk, and blast radius?\n- [ ] Which attractive ideas should be ruled out because the runtime surface is unsuitable or existing infrastructure already owns the behavior?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do not implement plugins or hooks.\n- Do not propose candidates without a real skill source and concrete runtime surface.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy: Plugin and Hook Opportunities\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n\nIdentify additional OpenCode plugins and Claude hooks grounded in existing `.opencode/skills/` contracts, and map every candidate to a concrete supported runtime hook surface.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n\n- [x] Which existing skills contain repeatable enforcement, routing, recovery, or quality logic that is currently manual or prompt-dependent?\n- [ ] Which additional OpenCode plugins are justified, and which exact `tool.execute.before/after`, `session.*`, or `experimental.*` surfaces should host them?\n- [ ] Which additional Claude hooks are justified, and which exact `PreToolUse`, `PostToolUse`, `SessionStart`, `UserPromptSubmit`, `Stop`, or `SessionEnd` surfaces should host them?\n- [ ] How should candidates be prioritized by value, feasibility, overlap, false-positive risk, and blast radius?\n- [ ] Which attractive ideas should be ruled out because the runtime surface is unsuitable or existing infrastructure already owns the behavior?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do not implement plugins or hooks.\n- Do not propose candidates without a real skill source and concrete runtime surface.\n- Do not treat undocumented runtime events as available.\n- Do not modify files outside this detached lineage directory.\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n\n- At least three evidence iterations have completed.\n- Every candidate is grounded in a cited skill and mapped to an allowed runtime surface.\n- OpenCode and Claude opportunities, prioritization, and eliminated alternatives are covered.\n- Convergence is legal under the configured policy, or five iterations have completed.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n\n- Which skill contracts are plausible automation candidates? Candidate families are mutation intake (`system-spec-kit`), destructive command safety (`sk-git`), post-edit quality (`code-quality`), and route/lifecycle validation (`system-skill-advisor`, `system-deep-loop`).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n\n- Current plugin inventory plus source-skill contract reads efficiently separated gaps from already-shipped behavior. (iteration 1)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n\n- The initial memory-context lookup timed out; repository evidence is the fallback.\n- Broad hook-term search was noisy because generated and archived artifacts dominated results. (iteration 1)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n\n- Generic prompt-context plugin: overlaps advisor, memory, code-graph, and goal entrypoints. (iteration 1)\n- Hook-owned deep-loop convergence: violates mode-packet and runtime ownership. (iteration 1)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Saturated: none yet\n- Remaining frontier: exact OpenCode mapping, Claude mapping, prioritization, and risk controls\n<!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n\n- Which OpenCode surface best fits each candidate while preserving current plugin ownership?\n- Which Claude surface provides equivalent timing without pretending runtime parity?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n\nMap concrete OpenCode plugin candidates to `tool.execute.before/after`, `session.*`, or `experimental.*`, validating feasibility and overlap against current entrypoints.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n\n- The requested runtime surface set is closed: OpenCode `tool.execute.before/after`, `session.*`, `experimental.*`; Claude `PreToolUse`, `PostToolUse`, `SessionStart`, `UserPromptSubmit`, `Stop`, `SessionEnd`.\n- Every candidate must cite a real skill under `.opencode/skills/`.\n- Memory context was unavailable after timeout; direct repository evidence is authoritative for this lineage.\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n\n- Max iterations: 5\n- Minimum iterations: 3\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05\n- Stop policy: convergence\n- Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n- Allowed write root: `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol`\n- Executor: `cli-opencode`, model `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast`\n- Session: `fanout-gptsol-1783743995827-g7k8yl`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":102,"totalLines":102,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1783744396231,"end":1783744396233}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b473eae8e75e964016a51c78c09348191ae63eb9e07933f5a"}},"id":"prt_f4f737b9d001Xm6fjsRl8Cua9v","sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","messageID":"msg_f4f7346bd001QRNhgBYqYi0PtE"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783744396365,"sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_oLGAlLkbERn0Gr8gGkxs7o6S","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js","offset":1,"limit":520},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n2: // ║ COMPONENT: mk-deep-loop-guard OpenCode Plugin (adapter)                  ║\n3: // ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n4: // ║ PURPOSE: OpenCode transport adapter over the runtime-neutral deep-loop   ║\n5: // ║          dispatch-guard core. Detection-layer enforcement for Task-tool  ║\n6: // ║          dispatches targeting deep-loop sub-agents -- flags/blocks a     ║\n7: // ║          Deep Route header whose declared mode disagrees with           ║\n8: // ║          mode-registry.json for the resolved target agent, and          ║\n9: // ║          flags/blocks repeated/loop-like non-command-driven dispatches   ║\n10: // ║          to command-owned loop executors within a session while         ║\n11: // ║          allowing one bounded hand-off. The parsing + policy + state    ║\n12: // ║          maintenance live in the shared core so the Claude PreToolUse   ║\n13: // ║          Task hook enforces the identical policy; this file only maps    ║\n14: // ║          OpenCode's tool.execute.before / session.created transport onto ║\n15: // ║          it. Stays default-export-only and never writes stdout/stderr:   ║\n16: // ║          a policy denial becomes a thrown error and a warning becomes a  ║\n17: // ║          bounded state-dir log line, never console output.              ║\n18: // ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n19: 'use strict';\n20: \n21: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n22: // 1. IMPORTS\n23: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n24: \n25: // The guard policy lives outside .opencode/plugins/ so this file can remain a\n26: // thin, default-export-only OpenCode plugin while the Claude hook consumes the\n27: // same core. A .cjs core is imported here as the ESM default export.\n28: import guardCore from '../skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/dispatch-guard.cjs';\n29: \n30: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n31: // 2. PLUGIN FACTORY\n32: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n33: \n34: /**\n35:  * Create the mk-deep-loop-guard OpenCode plugin hooks.\n36:  *\n37:  * Hard limits (by design, not oversight):\n38:  * - Cannot create hard runtime identity; that remains host/FIX-5 territory.\n39:  * - Does not catch a schema-valid, route-matched artifact that internally\n40:  *   does semantically wrong-mode work.\n41:  * - Loop-repeat detection is session-scoped and per-target-agent; it cannot\n42:  *   detect a cross-executor meta-loop (e.g. deep-research, deep-review,\n43:  *   deep-research again) -- only repeated hand-offs to the SAME executor.\n44:  * - Fails open on its own errors (missing/unreadable registry or state,\n45:  *   unexpected arg shapes) so a bug here never blocks unrelated, correctly-\n46:  *   routed work. Reject enforcement is best-effort and emits an audit line when\n47:  *   a required dependency is unavailable.\n48:  *\n49:  * @param {{ directory?: string } | undefined} ctx - OpenCode plugin context.\n50:  * @returns {Promise<object>} Hooks object for the OpenCode plugin loader.\n51:  */\n52: export default async function MkDeepLoopGuardPlugin(ctx) {\n53:   const projectDir = ctx?.directory || process.cwd();\n54:   const { stateDir: loopStateDir } = guardCore.resolveGuardPaths(projectDir);\n55:   const runtimeState = { lastLoopGuardSweepAtMs: 0 };\n56: \n57:   return {\n58:     async event(input = {}) {\n59:       try {\n60:         const type = input?.event?.type || input?.type;\n61:         if (type === 'session.created') guardCore.sweepStaleLoopGuardStates(loopStateDir, runtimeState);\n62:       } catch (_) {\n63:         // Fail open: a sweep error must never affect session startup.\n64:       }\n65:     },\n66:     async 'tool.execute.before'(input, output) {\n67:       try {\n68:         // Normalize tool-name case at the transport boundary (OpenCode emits\n69:         // 'task'; the Claude adapter handles its own 'Task').\n70:         if (!input || String(input.tool).toLowerCase() !== 'task') return;\n71:         const args = output && output.args;\n72:         if (!args || typeof args !== 'object') return;\n73: \n74:         const result = guardCore.evaluateDispatch({\n75:           subagentType: args.subagent_type || args.subagentType,\n76:           prompt: args.prompt,\n77:           sessionID: input.sessionID,\n78:           projectDir,\n79:           env: process.env,\n80:         });\n81: \n82:         for (const audit of result.audits) guardCore.appendRejectModeDegradedAudit(loopStateDir, audit);\n83:         for (const warning of result.warnings) guardCore.appendWarningLog(loopStateDir, warning);\n84: \n85:         if (result.decision === 'reject') throw new Error(result.detail);\n86:       } catch (err) {\n87:         if (err instanceof Error && err.message.startsWith('mk-deep-loop-guard:')) throw err;\n88:         // Fail open on any unexpected internal error -- never block unrelated dispatches.\n89:       }\n90:     },\n91:   };\n92: }\n\n(End of file - total 92 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ COMPONENT: mk-deep-loop-guard OpenCode Plugin (adapter)                  ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ PURPOSE: OpenCode transport adapter over the runtime-neutral deep-loop   ║\n// ║          dispatch-guard core. Detection-layer enforcement for Task-tool  ║\n// ║          dispatches targeting deep-loop sub-agents -- flags/blocks a     ║\n// ║          Deep Route header whose declared mode disagrees with           ║\n// ║          mode-registry.json for the resolved target agent, and          ║\n// ║          flags/blocks repeated/loop-like non-command-driven dispatches   ║\n// ║          to command-owned loop executors within a session while         ║\n// ║          allowing one bounded hand-off. The parsing + policy + state    ║\n// ║          maintenance live in the shared core so the Claude PreToolUse   ║\n// ║          Task hook enforces the identical policy; this file only maps    ║\n// ║          OpenCode's tool.execute.before / session.created transport onto ║\n// ║          it. Stays default-export-only and never writes stdout/stderr:   ║\n// ║          a policy denial becomes a thrown error and a warning becomes a  ║\n// ║          bounded state-dir log line, never console output.              ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n'use strict';\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js","text":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ COMPONENT: mk-deep-loop-guard OpenCode Plugin (adapter)                  ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ PURPOSE: OpenCode transport adapter over the runtime-neutral deep-loop   ║\n// ║          dispatch-guard core. Detection-layer enforcement for Task-tool  ║\n// ║          dispatches targeting deep-loop sub-agents -- flags/blocks a     ║\n// ║          Deep Route header whose declared mode disagrees with           ║\n// ║          mode-registry.json for the resolved target agent, and          ║\n// ║          flags/blocks repeated/loop-like non-command-driven dispatches   ║\n// ║          to command-owned loop executors within a session while         ║\n// ║          allowing one bounded hand-off. The parsing + policy + state    ║\n// ║          maintenance live in the shared core so the Claude PreToolUse   ║\n// ║          Task hook enforces the identical policy; this file only maps    ║\n// ║          OpenCode's tool.execute.before / session.created transport onto ║\n// ║          it. Stays default-export-only and never writes stdout/stderr:   ║\n// ║          a policy denial becomes a thrown error and a warning becomes a  ║\n// ║          bounded state-dir log line, never console output.              ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n'use strict';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. IMPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n// The guard policy lives outside .opencode/plugins/ so this file can remain a\n// thin, default-export-only OpenCode plugin while the Claude hook consumes the\n// same core. A .cjs core is imported here as the ESM default export.\nimport guardCore from '../skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/dispatch-guard.cjs';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 2. PLUGIN FACTORY\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * Create the mk-deep-loop-guard OpenCode plugin hooks.\n *\n * Hard limits (by design, not oversight):\n * - Cannot create hard runtime identity; that remains host/FIX-5 territory.\n * - Does not catch a schema-valid, route-matched artifact that internally\n *   does semantically wrong-mode work.\n * - Loop-repeat detection is session-scoped and per-target-agent; it cannot\n *   detect a cross-executor meta-loop (e.g. deep-research, deep-review,\n *   deep-research again) -- only repeated hand-offs to the SAME executor.\n * - Fails open on its own errors (missing/unreadable registry or state,\n *   unexpected arg shapes) so a bug here never blocks unrelated, correctly-\n *   routed work. Reject enforcement is best-effort and emits an audit line when\n *   a required dependency is unavailable.\n *\n * @param {{ directory?: string } | undefined} ctx - OpenCode plugin context.\n * @returns {Promise<object>} Hooks object for the OpenCode plugin loader.\n */\nexport default async function MkDeepLoopGuardPlugin(ctx) {\n  const projectDir = ctx?.directory || process.cwd();\n  const { stateDir: loopStateDir } = guardCore.resolveGuardPaths(projectDir);\n  const runtimeState = { lastLoopGuardSweepAtMs: 0 };\n\n  return {\n    async event(input = {}) {\n      try {\n        const type = input?.event?.type || input?.type;\n        if (type === 'session.created') guardCore.sweepStaleLoopGuardStates(loopStateDir, runtimeState);\n      } catch (_) {\n        // Fail open: a sweep error must never affect session startup.\n      }\n    },\n    async 'tool.execute.before'(input, output) {\n      try {\n        // Normalize tool-name case at the transport boundary (OpenCode emits\n        // 'task'; the Claude adapter handles its own 'Task').\n        if (!input || String(input.tool).toLowerCase() !== 'task') return;\n        const args = output && output.args;\n        if (!args || typeof args !== 'object') return;\n\n        const result = guardCore.evaluateDispatch({\n          subagentType: args.subagent_type || args.subagentType,\n          prompt: args.prompt,\n          sessionID: input.sessionID,\n          projectDir,\n          env: process.env,\n        });\n\n        for (const audit of result.audits) guardCore.appendRejectModeDegradedAudit(loopStateDir, audit);\n        for (const warning of result.warnings) guardCore.appendWarningLog(loopStateDir, warning);\n\n        if (result.decision === 'reject') throw new Error(result.detail);\n      } catch (err) {\n        if (err instanceof Error && err.message.startsWith('mk-deep-loop-guard:')) throw err;\n        // Fail open on any unexpected internal error -- never block unrelated dispatches.\n      }\n    },\n  };\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":92,"totalLines":92,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js","time":{"start":1783744396358,"end":1783744396364}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b473eae8e75e964016a51c78c09388191b1f3c050a53920a7"}},"id":"prt_f4f737c31001VG1tulzVtn9Wjz","sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","messageID":"msg_f4f7346bd001QRNhgBYqYi0PtE"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783744396376,"sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_o3xauOk5lsMRx0nIuPfbxLy9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/plugins/mk-dist-freshness-guard.js","offset":1,"limit":420},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/plugins/mk-dist-freshness-guard.js</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n2: // ║ COMPONENT: mk-dist-freshness-guard OpenCode Plugin                      ║\n3: // ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n4: // ║ PURPOSE: Warn when Bash dispatches or new sessions are about to trust    ║\n5: // ║          stale local dist outputs. The signal reaches the agent through  ║\n6: // ║          bounded system-context injection and an auditable log file --   ║\n7: // ║          never the terminal (see appendGuardLog for why).                ║\n8: // ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n9: 'use strict';\n10: \n11: import { createRequire } from 'node:module';\n12: import { appendFileSync, copyFileSync, mkdirSync, statSync, truncateSync } from 'node:fs';\n13: import { dirname, join, resolve } from 'node:path';\n14: import { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';\n15: \n16: const require = createRequire(import.meta.url);\n17: const {\n18:   checkAllFreshness,\n19:   formatCheckError,\n20:   formatWarning,\n21:   packageForSourceFile,\n22: } = require('../skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/lib/dist-freshness.cjs');\n23: \n24: const RISKY_BASH_COMMAND_REGEX = /opencode\\s+run|\\bvalidate\\.sh\\b/i;\n25: const PLUGIN_DIR = dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\n26: const WARN_LOG_RELATIVE = join('.opencode', 'logs', 'dist-freshness-guard.log');\n27: const MAX_GUARD_LOG_BYTES = 256 * 1024;\n28: const MAX_SESSION_IDS = 1_000;\n29: const MAX_DIAGNOSTIC_LINES = 8;\n30: const MUTATING_TOOLS = new Set(['write', 'edit', 'patch', 'multiedit', 'apply_patch', 'apply-patch']);\n31: // Re-hashing every watched package's sources is far too costly to run on every\n32: // chat turn, so the per-turn system-context injection reuses a short-lived cache\n33: // that the bounded bash/session triggers force-refresh.\n34: const STALE_CACHE_TTL_MS = 120_000;\n35: \n36: function commandTextFromArgs(args) {\n37:   if (!args || typeof args !== 'object') return '';\n38:   if (typeof args.command === 'string') return args.command;\n39:   try {\n40:     return JSON.stringify(args);\n41:   } catch (_) {\n42:     return '';\n43:   }\n44: }\n45: \n46: function eventPayloadFrom(input) {\n47:   if (input?.event && typeof input.event === 'object') return input.event;\n48:   if (input?.payload && typeof input.payload === 'object') return input.payload;\n49:   return input || {};\n50: }\n51: \n52: function eventTypeFrom(input) {\n53:   const payload = eventPayloadFrom(input);\n54:   return typeof payload.type === 'string' ? payload.type : null;\n55: }\n56: \n57: function sessionIdFromEvent(input) {\n58:   const payload = eventPayloadFrom(input);\n59:   const properties = payload.properties && typeof payload.properties === 'object' ? payload.properties : {};\n60:   const info = properties.info && typeof properties.info === 'object' ? properties.info : {};\n61:   return payload.sessionID || payload.sessionId || payload.session?.id\n62:     || properties.sessionID || properties.sessionId || properties.session?.id\n63:     || info.sessionID || info.sessionId || info.id || '__unknown-session__';\n64: }\n65: \n66: function freshnessDiagnostics(projectDir) {\n67:   return checkAllFreshness({ workspaceRoot: projectDir })\n68:     .filter((result) => result.stale || result.status === 'error');\n69: }\n70: \n71: function formatDiagnostic(result) {\n72:   return result?.status === 'error' ? formatCheckError(result) : formatWarning(result);\n73: }\n74: \n75: // Plugin warnings must never reach stdout/stderr: OpenCode's TUI paints plugin\n76: // console output onto the prompt input line, where it sticks until a redraw and\n77: // corrupts the interactive session. Persisting to a workspace log keeps the\n78: // signal auditable, and the system-context injection makes it actionable for the\n79: // agent. Fail-open -- a logging error must never affect the guarded work.\n80: function appendGuardLog(projectDir, detail) {\n81:   try {\n82:     const logPath = join(projectDir, WARN_LOG_RELATIVE);\n83:     mkdirSync(dirname(logPath), { recursive: true });\n84:     try {\n85:       if (statSync(logPath).size >= MAX_GUARD_LOG_BYTES) {\n86:         copyFileSync(logPath, `${logPath}.1`);\n87:         truncateSync(logPath, 0);\n88:       }\n89:     } catch (_) {\n90:       // A missing active log is the normal first-write case.\n91:     }\n92:     appendFileSync(logPath, `${new Date().toISOString()} [mk-dist-freshness-guard] ${detail}\\n`, 'utf8');\n93:   } catch (_) {\n94:     // Swallow: an audit-log failure must not disturb the session it observes.\n95:   }\n96: }\n97: \n98: function buildBrief(diagnostics) {\n99:   if (!Array.isArray(diagnostics) || diagnostics.length === 0) return '';\n100:   const stale = diagnostics.filter((result) => result.stale).map(formatWarning).filter(Boolean);\n101:   const errors = diagnostics.filter((result) => result.status === 'error').map(formatCheckError).filter(Boolean);\n102:   const lines = [];\n103:   if (stale.length > 0) {\n104:     lines.push('[dist-freshness-guard] Local compiled dist is stale; affected outputs may be untrustworthy until rebuilt:');\n105:     lines.push(...stale.map((line) => `- ${line}`));\n106:   }\n107:   if (errors.length > 0) {\n108:     lines.push('[dist-freshness-guard] CHECK ERROR: freshness could not be verified for every package:');\n109:     lines.push(...errors.map((line) => `- ${line}`));\n110:   }\n111:   return lines.slice(0, MAX_DIAGNOSTIC_LINES + 2).join('\\n');\n112: }\n113: \n114: export default async function MkDistFreshnessGuardPlugin(ctx) {\n115:   const projectDir = ctx?.directory || join(PLUGIN_DIR, '..', '..');\n116:   const sessionWarned = new Set();\n117:   // Per-instance freshness cache so multiple sessions in one process never share\n118:   // a mismatched projectDir result.\n119:   let diagnosticCache = null;\n120:   let diagnosticCheckedAt = 0;\n121: \n122:   function refreshDiagnostics(prefix) {\n123:     try {\n124:       diagnosticCache = freshnessDiagnostics(projectDir);\n125:     } catch (error) {\n126:       diagnosticCache = [{\n127:         packageId: null,\n128:         packageName: null,\n129:         status: 'error',\n130:         stale: false,\n131:         message: error?.message || String(error),\n132:       }];\n133:     }\n134:     diagnosticCheckedAt = Date.now();\n135:     if (diagnosticCache.length > 0) {\n136:       const details = diagnosticCache.map(formatDiagnostic).filter(Boolean).slice(0, MAX_DIAGNOSTIC_LINES).join('; ');\n137:       if (details) appendGuardLog(projectDir, `${prefix}: ${details}`);\n138:     }\n139:     return diagnosticCache;\n140:   }\n141: \n142:   function diagnosticsForInjection() {\n143:     if (diagnosticCache === null || (Date.now() - diagnosticCheckedAt) >= STALE_CACHE_TTL_MS) {\n144:       return refreshDiagnostics('inject');\n145:     }\n146:     return diagnosticCache;\n147:   }\n148: \n149:   function invalidateMutation(input, output) {\n150:     const tool = typeof input?.tool === 'string' ? input.tool.toLowerCase() : '';\n151:     if (!MUTATING_TOOLS.has(tool)) return false;\n152:     const args = output?.args;\n153:     const filePath = args && typeof args === 'object'\n154:       ? args.filePath || args.file_path || args.path\n155:       : null;\n156:     if (typeof filePath === 'string' && filePath\n157:       && !packageForSourceFile(resolve(projectDir, filePath), { workspaceRoot: projectDir })) return false;\n158:     diagnosticCache = null;\n159:     diagnosticCheckedAt = 0;\n160:     return true;\n161:   }\n162: \n163:   function rememberSession(sessionId) {\n164:     if (sessionWarned.has(sessionId)) return false;\n165:     if (sessionWarned.size >= MAX_SESSION_IDS) {\n166:       sessionWarned.delete(sessionWarned.values().next().value);\n167:     }\n168:     sessionWarned.add(sessionId);\n169:     return true;\n170:   }\n171: \n172:   return {\n173:     async 'tool.execute.before'(input, output) {\n174:       try {\n175:         if (invalidateMutation(input, output)) return;\n176:         if (!input || String(input.tool).toLowerCase() !== 'bash') return;\n177:         const commandText = commandTextFromArgs(output?.args);\n178:         if (!RISKY_BASH_COMMAND_REGEX.test(commandText)) return;\n179:         refreshDiagnostics('risky-bash');\n180:       } catch (error) {\n181:         appendGuardLog(projectDir, `freshness check failed: ${error?.message || error}`);\n182:       }\n183:     },\n184: \n185:     async event(input) {\n186:       try {\n187:         const eventType = eventTypeFrom(input);\n188:         if (eventType === 'session.deleted') {\n189:           sessionWarned.delete(String(sessionIdFromEvent(input)));\n190:           return;\n191:         }\n192:         if (eventType === 'server.instance.disposed' || eventType === 'global.disposed') {\n193:           sessionWarned.clear();\n194:           diagnosticCache = null;\n195:           diagnosticCheckedAt = 0;\n196:           return;\n197:         }\n198:         if (eventType !== 'session.created') return;\n199:         const sessionId = String(sessionIdFromEvent(input));\n200:         if (!rememberSession(sessionId)) return;\n201:         refreshDiagnostics('session.created');\n202:       } catch (error) {\n203:         appendGuardLog(projectDir, `session freshness check failed: ${error?.message || error}`);\n204:       }\n205:     },\n206: \n207:     async 'experimental.chat.system.transform'(input, output) {\n208:       try {\n209:         const brief = buildBrief(diagnosticsForInjection());\n210:         if (!brief || !output || typeof output !== 'object') return;\n211:         output.system = Array.isArray(output.system) ? output.system : [];\n212:         output.system.push(brief);\n213:       } catch (error) {\n214:         appendGuardLog(projectDir, `system transform failed: ${error?.message || error}`);\n215:       }\n216:     },\n217:   };\n218: }\n\n(End of file - total 218 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ COMPONENT: mk-dist-freshness-guard OpenCode Plugin                      ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ PURPOSE: Warn when Bash dispatches or new sessions are about to trust    ║\n// ║          stale local dist outputs. The signal reaches the agent through  ║\n// ║          bounded system-context injection and an auditable log file --   ║\n// ║          never the terminal (see appendGuardLog for why).                ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n'use strict';\n\nimport { createRequire } from 'node:module';\nimport { appendFileSync, copyFileSync, mkdirSync, statSync, truncateSync } from 'node:fs';\nimport { dirname, join, resolve } from 'node:path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';\n\nconst require = createRequire(import.meta.url);\nconst {\n  checkAllFreshness,\n  formatCheckError,\n  formatWarning,","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/plugins/mk-dist-freshness-guard.js","text":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ COMPONENT: mk-dist-freshness-guard OpenCode Plugin                      ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ PURPOSE: Warn when Bash dispatches or new sessions are about to trust    ║\n// ║          stale local dist outputs. The signal reaches the agent through  ║\n// ║          bounded system-context injection and an auditable log file --   ║\n// ║          never the terminal (see appendGuardLog for why).                ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n'use strict';\n\nimport { createRequire } from 'node:module';\nimport { appendFileSync, copyFileSync, mkdirSync, statSync, truncateSync } from 'node:fs';\nimport { dirname, join, resolve } from 'node:path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';\n\nconst require = createRequire(import.meta.url);\nconst {\n  checkAllFreshness,\n  formatCheckError,\n  formatWarning,\n  packageForSourceFile,\n} = require('../skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/lib/dist-freshness.cjs');\n\nconst RISKY_BASH_COMMAND_REGEX = /opencode\\s+run|\\bvalidate\\.sh\\b/i;\nconst PLUGIN_DIR = dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\nconst WARN_LOG_RELATIVE = join('.opencode', 'logs', 'dist-freshness-guard.log');\nconst MAX_GUARD_LOG_BYTES = 256 * 1024;\nconst MAX_SESSION_IDS = 1_000;\nconst MAX_DIAGNOSTIC_LINES = 8;\nconst MUTATING_TOOLS = new Set(['write', 'edit', 'patch', 'multiedit', 'apply_patch', 'apply-patch']);\n// Re-hashing every watched package's sources is far too costly to run on every\n// chat turn, so the per-turn system-context injection reuses a short-lived cache\n// that the bounded bash/session triggers force-refresh.\nconst STALE_CACHE_TTL_MS = 120_000;\n\nfunction commandTextFromArgs(args) {\n  if (!args || typeof args !== 'object') return '';\n  if (typeof args.command === 'string') return args.command;\n  try {\n    return JSON.stringify(args);\n  } catch (_) {\n    return '';\n  }\n}\n\nfunction eventPayloadFrom(input) {\n  if (input?.event && typeof input.event === 'object') return input.event;\n  if (input?.payload && typeof input.payload === 'object') return input.payload;\n  return input || {};\n}\n\nfunction eventTypeFrom(input) {\n  const payload = eventPayloadFrom(input);\n  return typeof payload.type === 'string' ? payload.type : null;\n}\n\nfunction sessionIdFromEvent(input) {\n  const payload = eventPayloadFrom(input);\n  const properties = payload.properties && typeof payload.properties === 'object' ? payload.properties : {};\n  const info = properties.info && typeof properties.info === 'object' ? properties.info : {};\n  return payload.sessionID || payload.sessionId || payload.session?.id\n    || properties.sessionID || properties.sessionId || properties.session?.id\n    || info.sessionID || info.sessionId || info.id || '__unknown-session__';\n}\n\nfunction freshnessDiagnostics(projectDir) {\n  return checkAllFreshness({ workspaceRoot: projectDir })\n    .filter((result) => result.stale || result.status === 'error');\n}\n\nfunction formatDiagnostic(result) {\n  return result?.status === 'error' ? formatCheckError(result) : formatWarning(result);\n}\n\n// Plugin warnings must never reach stdout/stderr: OpenCode's TUI paints plugin\n// console output onto the prompt input line, where it sticks until a redraw and\n// corrupts the interactive session. Persisting to a workspace log keeps the\n// signal auditable, and the system-context injection makes it actionable for the\n// agent. Fail-open -- a logging error must never affect the guarded work.\nfunction appendGuardLog(projectDir, detail) {\n  try {\n    const logPath = join(projectDir, WARN_LOG_RELATIVE);\n    mkdirSync(dirname(logPath), { recursive: true });\n    try {\n      if (statSync(logPath).size >= MAX_GUARD_LOG_BYTES) {\n        copyFileSync(logPath, `${logPath}.1`);\n        truncateSync(logPath, 0);\n      }\n    } catch (_) {\n      // A missing active log is the normal first-write case.\n    }\n    appendFileSync(logPath, `${new Date().toISOString()} [mk-dist-freshness-guard] ${detail}\\n`, 'utf8');\n  } catch (_) {\n    // Swallow: an audit-log failure must not disturb the session it observes.\n  }\n}\n\nfunction buildBrief(diagnostics) {\n  if (!Array.isArray(diagnostics) || diagnostics.length === 0) return '';\n  const stale = diagnostics.filter((result) => result.stale).map(formatWarning).filter(Boolean);\n  const errors = diagnostics.filter((result) => result.status === 'error').map(formatCheckError).filter(Boolean);\n  const lines = [];\n  if (stale.length > 0) {\n    lines.push('[dist-freshness-guard] Local compiled dist is stale; affected outputs may be untrustworthy until rebuilt:');\n    lines.push(...stale.map((line) => `- ${line}`));\n  }\n  if (errors.length > 0) {\n    lines.push('[dist-freshness-guard] CHECK ERROR: freshness could not be verified for every package:');\n    lines.push(...errors.map((line) => `- ${line}`));\n  }\n  return lines.slice(0, MAX_DIAGNOSTIC_LINES + 2).join('\\n');\n}\n\nexport default async function MkDistFreshnessGuardPlugin(ctx) {\n  const projectDir = ctx?.directory || join(PLUGIN_DIR, '..', '..');\n  const sessionWarned = new Set();\n  // Per-instance freshness cache so multiple sessions in one process never share\n  // a mismatched projectDir result.\n  let diagnosticCache = null;\n  let diagnosticCheckedAt = 0;\n\n  function refreshDiagnostics(prefix) {\n    try {\n      diagnosticCache = freshnessDiagnostics(projectDir);\n    } catch (error) {\n      diagnosticCache = [{\n        packageId: null,\n        packageName: null,\n        status: 'error',\n        stale: false,\n        message: error?.message || String(error),\n      }];\n    }\n    diagnosticCheckedAt = Date.now();\n    if (diagnosticCache.length > 0) {\n      const details = diagnosticCache.map(formatDiagnostic).filter(Boolean).slice(0, MAX_DIAGNOSTIC_LINES).join('; ');\n      if (details) appendGuardLog(projectDir, `${prefix}: ${details}`);\n    }\n    return diagnosticCache;\n  }\n\n  function diagnosticsForInjection() {\n    if (diagnosticCache === null || (Date.now() - diagnosticCheckedAt) >= STALE_CACHE_TTL_MS) {\n      return refreshDiagnostics('inject');\n    }\n    return diagnosticCache;\n  }\n\n  function invalidateMutation(input, output) {\n    const tool = typeof input?.tool === 'string' ? input.tool.toLowerCase() : '';\n    if (!MUTATING_TOOLS.has(tool)) return false;\n    const args = output?.args;\n    const filePath = args && typeof args === 'object'\n      ? args.filePath || args.file_path || args.path\n      : null;\n    if (typeof filePath === 'string' && filePath\n      && !packageForSourceFile(resolve(projectDir, filePath), { workspaceRoot: projectDir })) return false;\n    diagnosticCache = null;\n    diagnosticCheckedAt = 0;\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  function rememberSession(sessionId) {\n    if (sessionWarned.has(sessionId)) return false;\n    if (sessionWarned.size >= MAX_SESSION_IDS) {\n      sessionWarned.delete(sessionWarned.values().next().value);\n    }\n    sessionWarned.add(sessionId);\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  return {\n    async 'tool.execute.before'(input, output) {\n      try {\n        if (invalidateMutation(input, output)) return;\n        if (!input || String(input.tool).toLowerCase() !== 'bash') return;\n        const commandText = commandTextFromArgs(output?.args);\n        if (!RISKY_BASH_COMMAND_REGEX.test(commandText)) return;\n        refreshDiagnostics('risky-bash');\n      } catch (error) {\n        appendGuardLog(projectDir, `freshness check failed: ${error?.message || error}`);\n      }\n    },\n\n    async event(input) {\n      try {\n        const eventType = eventTypeFrom(input);\n        if (eventType === 'session.deleted') {\n          sessionWarned.delete(String(sessionIdFromEvent(input)));\n          return;\n        }\n        if (eventType === 'server.instance.disposed' || eventType === 'global.disposed') {\n          sessionWarned.clear();\n          diagnosticCache = null;\n          diagnosticCheckedAt = 0;\n          return;\n        }\n        if (eventType !== 'session.created') return;\n        const sessionId = String(sessionIdFromEvent(input));\n        if (!rememberSession(sessionId)) return;\n        refreshDiagnostics('session.created');\n      } catch (error) {\n        appendGuardLog(projectDir, `session freshness check failed: ${error?.message || error}`);\n      }\n    },\n\n    async 'experimental.chat.system.transform'(input, output) {\n      try {\n        const brief = buildBrief(diagnosticsForInjection());\n        if (!brief || !output || typeof output !== 'object') return;\n        output.system = Array.isArray(output.system) ? output.system : [];\n        output.system.push(brief);\n      } catch (error) {\n        appendGuardLog(projectDir, `system transform failed: ${error?.message || error}`);\n      }\n    },\n  };\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":218,"totalLines":218,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/plugins/mk-dist-freshness-guard.js","time":{"start":1783744396373,"end":1783744396375}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b473eae8e75e964016a51c78c093c819182544838e33acaba"}},"id":"prt_f4f737c4a001UHzFeBSRXDkAZJ","sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","messageID":"msg_f4f7346bd001QRNhgBYqYi0PtE"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783744396390,"sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_4fokUXn4dfFn4XPU0z16ZIBS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/plugins/mk-goal.js","offset":760,"limit":360},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/plugins/mk-goal.js</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n760:   try {\n761:     const stateDir = await ensureGoalStateDir(options);\n762:     const timestamp = isoFromMs(nowMs(options));\n763:     const entry = {\n764:       ts: timestamp,\n765:       goalId: payload?.goalId === undefined ? null : payload.goalId,\n766:       ...payload,\n767:     };\n768:     const line = `${JSON.stringify(entry)}\\n`;\n769:     const path = join(stateDir, filename);\n770:     const previous = jsonlAppendQueues.get(path) || Promise.resolve();\n771:     const run = previous.catch(() => undefined).then(async () => {\n772:       await pruneJsonlLog(filename, stateDir, options);\n773:       await rotateJsonlLog(filename, stateDir, Buffer.byteLength(line), options);\n774:       await appendFile(path, line, 'utf8');\n775:     });\n776:     jsonlAppendQueues.set(path, run);\n777:     try {\n778:       await run;\n779:     } finally {\n780:       if (jsonlAppendQueues.get(path) === run) jsonlAppendQueues.delete(path);\n781:     }\n782:   } catch (error) {\n783:     writeDebugStderr('appendGoalJsonl', error);\n784:     return;\n785:   }\n786: }\n787: \n788: async function rotateJsonlLog(filename, stateDir, incomingBytes, rawOptions = {}) {\n789:   if (!OWNED_JSONL_LOGS.has(filename)) return;\n790:   const options = normalizeOptions(rawOptions);\n791:   const path = join(stateDir, filename);\n792:   try {\n793:     const fileStats = await stat(path);\n794:     if (fileStats.size + incomingBytes <= options.jsonlMaxBytes) return;\n795:     const segmentPath = `${path}.${nowMs(options)}-${randomUUID()}`;\n796:     await rename(path, segmentPath);\n797:   } catch (error) {\n798:     if (error?.code !== 'ENOENT') throw error;\n799:   }\n800: }\n801: \n802: function writeDebugStderr(source, error) {\n803:   if (!process.env[DEBUG_ENV]) return;\n804:   try {\n805:     const message = redactEvidence(error?.message || 'unknown error', DEFAULT_MAX_REASON_CHARS);\n806:     process.stderr.write(`[mk-goal] ${source}: ${message}\\n`);\n807:   } catch {\n808:     return;\n809:   }\n810: }\n811: \n812: async function pruneJsonlLog(filename, stateDir, rawOptions = {}) {\n813:   if (!OWNED_JSONL_LOGS.has(filename)) return;\n814:   try {\n815:     const retentionMs = retentionDaysFromEnv(ARCHIVE_RETENTION_DAYS_ENV, DEFAULT_ARCHIVE_RETENTION_DAYS) * MS_PER_DAY;\n816:     const timestamp = retentionNowMs(rawOptions);\n817:     const path = join(stateDir, filename);\n818:     try {\n819:       const fileStats = await stat(path);\n820:       if (timestamp - fileStats.mtimeMs > retentionMs) await unlink(path);\n821:     } catch (error) {\n822:       if (error?.code !== 'ENOENT') throw error;\n823:     }\n824:     const entries = await readdir(stateDir, { withFileTypes: true });\n825:     await Promise.all(entries.map(async (entry) => {\n826:       if (!entry.isFile() || !entry.name.startsWith(`${filename}.`)) return;\n827:       const segmentPath = join(stateDir, entry.name);\n828:       const segmentStats = await stat(segmentPath);\n829:       if (timestamp - segmentStats.mtimeMs > retentionMs) await unlink(segmentPath);\n830:     }));\n831:   } catch {\n832:     return;\n833:   }\n834: }\n835: \n836: async function logContinuationDecision(sessionID, decision, reason, autoTurnsUsed, rawOptions = {}, goalId = null) {\n837:   if (QUIET_CONTINUATION_REASONS.has(reason)) return;\n838:   await appendGoalJsonl(CONTINUATION_LOG_FILENAME, {\n839:     sid: sessionID || null,\n840:     goalId: goalId || null,\n841:     decision,\n842:     reason: sanitizeInlineText(reason, DEFAULT_MAX_REASON_CHARS) || 'unknown',\n843:     autoTurnsUsed: normalizeAutoTurns(autoTurnsUsed),\n844:   }, rawOptions);\n845: }\n846: \n847: async function logDebugEvent(eventType, sessionID, rawOptions = {}) {\n848:   if (process.env[DEBUG_ENV] !== '1') return;\n849:   await appendGoalJsonl(GOAL_EVENTS_LOG_FILENAME, {\n850:     type: sanitizeInlineText(eventType || 'unknown', 80),\n851:     sid: sessionID || null,\n852:     goalId: null,\n853:   }, rawOptions);\n854: }\n855: \n856: async function logDebugEventError(event, error, rawOptions = {}) {\n857:   await appendGoalJsonl(GOAL_EVENTS_LOG_FILENAME, {\n858:     type: 'event_error',\n859:     eventType: sanitizeInlineText(eventTypeFrom(event) || 'unknown', 80),\n860:     sid: extractEventSessionID(event),\n861:     goalId: extractEventGoalID(event) || null,\n862:     error: redactEvidence(error?.message || 'unknown error', DEFAULT_MAX_REASON_CHARS),\n863:   }, rawOptions);\n864: }\n865: \n866: function numericField(source, keys) {\n867:   if (!source || typeof source !== 'object') return null;\n868:   for (const key of keys) {\n869:     const value = Number(source[key]);\n870:     if (Number.isFinite(value) && value > 0) return Math.trunc(value);\n871:   }\n872:   return null;\n873: }\n874: \n875: function tokenCountFromUsage(usage) {\n876:   if (!usage || typeof usage !== 'object') return 0;\n877:   const direct = numericField(usage, [\n878:     'tokenDelta',\n879:     'token_delta',\n880:     'tokensDelta',\n881:     'tokens_delta',\n882:     'totalTokens',\n883:     'total_tokens',\n884:     'tokens',\n885:     'tokenCount',\n886:     'token_count',\n887:   ]);\n888:   if (direct !== null) return direct;\n889:   const hasNativeFields = ['input', 'output', 'reasoning'].some((key) => Object.hasOwn(usage, key))\n890:     || (usage.cache && typeof usage.cache === 'object');\n891:   if (hasNativeFields) {\n892:     return (numericField(usage, ['input']) || 0)\n893:       + (numericField(usage, ['output']) || 0)\n894:       + (numericField(usage, ['reasoning']) || 0)\n895:       + (numericField(usage.cache, ['read']) || 0)\n896:       + (numericField(usage.cache, ['write']) || 0);\n897:   }\n898:   const input = numericField(usage, ['inputTokens', 'input_tokens', 'promptTokens', 'prompt_tokens']) || 0;\n899:   const output = numericField(usage, ['outputTokens', 'output_tokens', 'completionTokens', 'completion_tokens']) || 0;\n900:   return input + output;\n901: }\n902: \n903: function secondsFromUsage(usage) {\n904:   if (!usage || typeof usage !== 'object') return 0;\n905:   const direct = numericField(usage, ['timeSeconds', 'time_seconds', 'seconds', 'durationSeconds', 'duration_seconds']);\n906:   if (direct !== null) return direct;\n907:   const millis = numericField(usage, ['timeMs', 'time_ms', 'durationMs', 'duration_ms']);\n908:   return millis === null ? 0 : Math.max(1, Math.trunc(millis / 1000));\n909: }\n910: \n911: function extractUsageFromEvent(event) {\n912:   const payload = eventPayloadFrom(event);\n913:   const properties = eventPropertiesFrom(payload);\n914:   const candidates = [\n915:     payload?.usage,\n916:     payload?.message?.usage,\n917:     properties.usage,\n918:     properties.info?.usage,\n919:     properties.info?.tokens,\n920:     properties.message?.usage,\n921:     properties.part?.usage,\n922:   ].filter((candidate) => candidate && typeof candidate === 'object');\n923:   const usage = candidates.find((candidate) => tokenCountFromUsage(candidate) > 0) || candidates[0] || null;\n924:   const tokenDelta = tokenCountFromUsage(usage);\n925:   const timeDeltaSeconds = secondsFromUsage(usage);\n926:   const nativeUsage = usage === properties.info?.tokens;\n927:   const source = sanitizeInlineText(\n928:     usage?.source || usage?.usageSource || (nativeUsage ? 'opencode-native-tokens' : tokenDelta > 0 ? 'message.updated' : 'unavailable'),\n929:     80,\n930:   );\n931:   return {\n932:     tokenDelta,\n933:     timeDeltaSeconds,\n934:     usageSource: source || 'unavailable',\n935:   };\n936: }\n937: \n938: function extractErrorFromEvent(event) {\n939:   const payload = eventPayloadFrom(event);\n940:   const properties = eventPropertiesFrom(payload);\n941:   return [\n942:     payload?.error,\n943:     payload?.message?.error,\n944:     properties.error,\n945:     properties.info?.error,\n946:     properties.message?.error,\n947:     properties.part?.error,\n948:   ].find((candidate) => candidate && typeof candidate === 'object') || null;\n949: }\n950: \n951: function firstValue(source, keys) {\n952:   if (!source || typeof source !== 'object') return undefined;\n953:   for (const key of keys) {\n954:     if (source[key] !== undefined) return source[key];\n955:   }\n956:   return undefined;\n957: }\n958: \n959: function statusCodeFromError(error) {\n960:   const candidates = [\n961:     error?.statusCode,\n962:     error?.status,\n963:     error?.code,\n964:     error?.data?.statusCode,\n965:     error?.data?.status,\n966:     error?.response?.statusCode,\n967:     error?.response?.status,\n968:   ];\n969:   for (const candidate of candidates) {\n970:     const numeric = Number(candidate);\n971:     if (Number.isFinite(numeric)) return Math.trunc(numeric);\n972:   }\n973:   return null;\n974: }\n975: \n976: function errorMessageText(error) {\n977:   return [\n978:     error?.message,\n979:     error?.data?.message,\n980:     error?.data?.error,\n981:     error?.body?.message,\n982:     error?.response?.message,\n983:   ].map((entry) => (entry === null || entry === undefined ? '' : String(entry))).filter(Boolean).join(' ');\n984: }\n985: \n986: function isProviderUsageLimit(error) {\n987:   if (!error || typeof error !== 'object') return false;\n988:   if (statusCodeFromError(error) === 429) return true;\n989:   return /\\b(?:rate\\s*limit(?:ed)?|too many requests|usage[_ -]?limit(?:ed)?|insufficient quota|quota (?:exceeded|limit|reached))\\b/i.test(errorMessageText(error));\n990: }\n991: \n992: function retryAfterDeadlineFromValue(value, unit, rawOptions = {}) {\n993:   if (value === null || value === undefined || value === '') return null;\n994:   const timestamp = nowMs(rawOptions);\n995:   const numeric = Number(value);\n996:   if (Number.isFinite(numeric) && numeric > 0) {\n997:     const normalizedUnit = sanitizeInlineText(unit || '', 20).toLowerCase();\n998:     if (unit === 'ms') return Math.trunc(timestamp + numeric);\n999:     if (normalizedUnit === 'ms' || normalizedUnit === 'millisecond' || normalizedUnit === 'milliseconds') {\n1000:       return Math.trunc(timestamp + numeric);\n1001:     }\n1002:     if (normalizedUnit === 's' || normalizedUnit === 'sec' || normalizedUnit === 'second' || normalizedUnit === 'seconds') {\n1003:       return Math.trunc(timestamp + (numeric * 1000));\n1004:     }\n1005:     if (numeric > 1000000000000) return Math.trunc(numeric);\n1006:     return Math.trunc(timestamp + (numeric * 1000));\n1007:   }\n1008:   const dateMs = Date.parse(String(value));\n1009:   return Number.isFinite(dateMs) && dateMs > timestamp ? Math.trunc(dateMs) : null;\n1010: }\n1011: \n1012: function providerRetryAfterDeadlineMs(error, rawOptions = {}) {\n1013:   const headerRetryAfter = firstValue(error?.headers, ['retry-after', 'Retry-After'])\n1014:     ?? firstValue(error?.data?.headers, ['retry-after', 'Retry-After'])\n1015:     ?? firstValue(error?.response?.headers, ['retry-after', 'Retry-After']);\n1016:   const candidates = [\n1017:     [error?.retryAfterMs, 'ms'],\n1018:     [error?.data?.retryAfterMs, 'ms'],\n1019:     [error?.retryAfter, 'seconds'],\n1020:     [error?.retry_after, 'seconds'],\n1021:     [error?.data?.retryAfter, 'seconds'],\n1022:     [error?.data?.retry_after, 'seconds'],\n1023:     [headerRetryAfter, 'seconds'],\n1024:   ];\n1025:   for (const [value, unit] of candidates) {\n1026:     const deadline = retryAfterDeadlineFromValue(value, unit, rawOptions);\n1027:     if (deadline !== null) return deadline;\n1028:   }\n1029:   return null;\n1030: }\n1031: \n1032: function providerUsageLimitPatch(error, rawOptions = {}) {\n1033:   return {\n1034:     status: 'usage_limited',\n1035:     continuationSuppressed: true,\n1036:     continuationSuppressedReason: 'usage_limited',\n1037:     providerRetryAfterMs: providerRetryAfterDeadlineMs(error, rawOptions),\n1038:   };\n1039: }\n1040: \n1041: function roleFromObject(value) {\n1042:   if (!value || typeof value !== 'object') return null;\n1043:   return sanitizeInlineText(value.role || value.author?.role || value.sender?.role || '', 80).toLowerCase() || null;\n1044: }\n1045: \n1046: function textFromValue(value, depth = 0) {\n1047:   if (depth > 4 || value === null || value === undefined) return '';\n1048:   if (typeof value === 'string') return value;\n1049:   if (Array.isArray(value)) return value.map((entry) => textFromValue(entry, depth + 1)).filter(Boolean).join(' ');\n1050:   if (typeof value !== 'object') return '';\n1051:   for (const key of ['text', 'content', 'markdown', 'output', 'summary']) {\n1052:     const text = textFromValue(value[key], depth + 1);\n1053:     if (text) return text;\n1054:   }\n1055:   return '';\n1056: }\n1057: \n1058: function extractAssistantEvidence(event, rawOptions = {}) {\n1059:   const options = normalizeOptions(rawOptions);\n1060:   const payload = eventPayloadFrom(event);\n1061:   const properties = eventPropertiesFrom(payload);\n1062:   const candidates = [\n1063:     payload?.message,\n1064:     payload?.info,\n1065:     payload?.part,\n1066:     properties.message,\n1067:     properties.info,\n1068:     properties.part,\n1069:     payload,\n1070:   ].filter((candidate) => candidate && typeof candidate === 'object');\n1071:   const role = candidates.map(roleFromObject).find(Boolean);\n1072:   if (role && role !== 'assistant') return null;\n1073:   const text = candidates.map((candidate) => textFromValue(candidate)).find(Boolean);\n1074:   const redacted = redactEvidence(text, options.maxEvidenceChars);\n1075:   return redacted || null;\n1076: }\n1077: \n1078: function extractAssistantTextPartEvidence(event, rawOptions = {}) {\n1079:   const payload = eventPayloadFrom(event);\n1080:   const properties = eventPropertiesFrom(payload);\n1081:   const part = payload?.part || properties.part;\n1082:   if (!part || part.type !== 'text') return null;\n1083:   const role = [part, payload?.info, properties.info, payload].map(roleFromObject).find(Boolean);\n1084:   if (role !== 'assistant') return null;\n1085:   return extractAssistantEvidence(event, rawOptions);\n1086: }\n1087: \n1088: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1089: // 5. STATE STORE\n1090: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1091: \n1092: /**\n1093:  * Ensure the goal state directory exists.\n1094:  *\n1095:  * @param {Object} [rawOptions] - State helper options\n1096:  * @param {string} [rawOptions.stateDir] - Override directory for tests\n1097:  * @returns {Promise<string>} Absolute state directory path\n1098:  */\n1099: async function ensureGoalStateDir(rawOptions = {}) {\n1100:   const options = normalizeOptions(rawOptions);\n1101:   if (knownStateDirs.has(options.stateDir)) return options.stateDir;\n1102:   countMetric(options, 'mkdirStateDir');\n1103:   await mkdir(options.stateDir, { recursive: true, mode: 0o700 });\n1104:   knownStateDirs.add(options.stateDir);\n1105:   return options.stateDir;\n1106: }\n1107: \n1108: async function ensureGoalArchiveDir(rawOptions = {}) {\n1109:   const stateDir = await ensureGoalStateDir(rawOptions);\n1110:   const archiveDir = join(stateDir, '.archive');\n1111:   countMetric(rawOptions, 'mkdirArchiveDir');\n1112:   await mkdir(archiveDir, { recursive: true, mode: 0o700 });\n1113:   return archiveDir;\n1114: }\n1115: \n1116: /**\n1117:  * Resolve a per-session goal state file path.\n1118:  *\n1119:  * @param {string} sessionID - OpenCode session id\n\n(Showing lines 760-1119 of 2986. Use offset=1120 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"  try {\n    const stateDir = await ensureGoalStateDir(options);\n    const timestamp = isoFromMs(nowMs(options));\n    const entry = {\n      ts: timestamp,\n      goalId: payload?.goalId === undefined ? null : payload.goalId,\n      ...payload,\n    };\n    const line = `${JSON.stringify(entry)}\\n`;\n    const path = join(stateDir, filename);\n    const previous = jsonlAppendQueues.get(path) || Promise.resolve();\n    const run = previous.catch(() => undefined).then(async () => {\n      await pruneJsonlLog(filename, stateDir, options);\n      await rotateJsonlLog(filename, stateDir, Buffer.byteLength(line), options);\n      await appendFile(path, line, 'utf8');\n    });\n    jsonlAppendQueues.set(path, run);\n    try {\n      await run;\n    } finally {","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/plugins/mk-goal.js","text":"  try {\n    const stateDir = await ensureGoalStateDir(options);\n    const timestamp = isoFromMs(nowMs(options));\n    const entry = {\n      ts: timestamp,\n      goalId: payload?.goalId === undefined ? null : payload.goalId,\n      ...payload,\n    };\n    const line = `${JSON.stringify(entry)}\\n`;\n    const path = join(stateDir, filename);\n    const previous = jsonlAppendQueues.get(path) || Promise.resolve();\n    const run = previous.catch(() => undefined).then(async () => {\n      await pruneJsonlLog(filename, stateDir, options);\n      await rotateJsonlLog(filename, stateDir, Buffer.byteLength(line), options);\n      await appendFile(path, line, 'utf8');\n    });\n    jsonlAppendQueues.set(path, run);\n    try {\n      await run;\n    } finally {\n      if (jsonlAppendQueues.get(path) === run) jsonlAppendQueues.delete(path);\n    }\n  } catch (error) {\n    writeDebugStderr('appendGoalJsonl', error);\n    return;\n  }\n}\n\nasync function rotateJsonlLog(filename, stateDir, incomingBytes, rawOptions = {}) {\n  if (!OWNED_JSONL_LOGS.has(filename)) return;\n  const options = normalizeOptions(rawOptions);\n  const path = join(stateDir, filename);\n  try {\n    const fileStats = await stat(path);\n    if (fileStats.size + incomingBytes <= options.jsonlMaxBytes) return;\n    const segmentPath = `${path}.${nowMs(options)}-${randomUUID()}`;\n    await rename(path, segmentPath);\n  } catch (error) {\n    if (error?.code !== 'ENOENT') throw error;\n  }\n}\n\nfunction writeDebugStderr(source, error) {\n  if (!process.env[DEBUG_ENV]) return;\n  try {\n    const message = redactEvidence(error?.message || 'unknown error', DEFAULT_MAX_REASON_CHARS);\n    process.stderr.write(`[mk-goal] ${source}: ${message}\\n`);\n  } catch {\n    return;\n  }\n}\n\nasync function pruneJsonlLog(filename, stateDir, rawOptions = {}) {\n  if (!OWNED_JSONL_LOGS.has(filename)) return;\n  try {\n    const retentionMs = retentionDaysFromEnv(ARCHIVE_RETENTION_DAYS_ENV, DEFAULT_ARCHIVE_RETENTION_DAYS) * MS_PER_DAY;\n    const timestamp = retentionNowMs(rawOptions);\n    const path = join(stateDir, filename);\n    try {\n      const fileStats = await stat(path);\n      if (timestamp - fileStats.mtimeMs > retentionMs) await unlink(path);\n    } catch (error) {\n      if (error?.code !== 'ENOENT') throw error;\n    }\n    const entries = await readdir(stateDir, { withFileTypes: true });\n    await Promise.all(entries.map(async (entry) => {\n      if (!entry.isFile() || !entry.name.startsWith(`${filename}.`)) return;\n      const segmentPath = join(stateDir, entry.name);\n      const segmentStats = await stat(segmentPath);\n      if (timestamp - segmentStats.mtimeMs > retentionMs) await unlink(segmentPath);\n    }));\n  } catch {\n    return;\n  }\n}\n\nasync function logContinuationDecision(sessionID, decision, reason, autoTurnsUsed, rawOptions = {}, goalId = null) {\n  if (QUIET_CONTINUATION_REASONS.has(reason)) return;\n  await appendGoalJsonl(CONTINUATION_LOG_FILENAME, {\n    sid: sessionID || null,\n    goalId: goalId || null,\n    decision,\n    reason: sanitizeInlineText(reason, DEFAULT_MAX_REASON_CHARS) || 'unknown',\n    autoTurnsUsed: normalizeAutoTurns(autoTurnsUsed),\n  }, rawOptions);\n}\n\nasync function logDebugEvent(eventType, sessionID, rawOptions = {}) {\n  if (process.env[DEBUG_ENV] !== '1') return;\n  await appendGoalJsonl(GOAL_EVENTS_LOG_FILENAME, {\n    type: sanitizeInlineText(eventType || 'unknown', 80),\n    sid: sessionID || null,\n    goalId: null,\n  }, rawOptions);\n}\n\nasync function logDebugEventError(event, error, rawOptions = {}) {\n  await appendGoalJsonl(GOAL_EVENTS_LOG_FILENAME, {\n    type: 'event_error',\n    eventType: sanitizeInlineText(eventTypeFrom(event) || 'unknown', 80),\n    sid: extractEventSessionID(event),\n    goalId: extractEventGoalID(event) || null,\n    error: redactEvidence(error?.message || 'unknown error', DEFAULT_MAX_REASON_CHARS),\n  }, rawOptions);\n}\n\nfunction numericField(source, keys) {\n  if (!source || typeof source !== 'object') return null;\n  for (const key of keys) {\n    const value = Number(source[key]);\n    if (Number.isFinite(value) && value > 0) return Math.trunc(value);\n  }\n  return null;\n}\n\nfunction tokenCountFromUsage(usage) {\n  if (!usage || typeof usage !== 'object') return 0;\n  const direct = numericField(usage, [\n    'tokenDelta',\n    'token_delta',\n    'tokensDelta',\n    'tokens_delta',\n    'totalTokens',\n    'total_tokens',\n    'tokens',\n    'tokenCount',\n    'token_count',\n  ]);\n  if (direct !== null) return direct;\n  const hasNativeFields = ['input', 'output', 'reasoning'].some((key) => Object.hasOwn(usage, key))\n    || (usage.cache && typeof usage.cache === 'object');\n  if (hasNativeFields) {\n    return (numericField(usage, ['input']) || 0)\n      + (numericField(usage, ['output']) || 0)\n      + (numericField(usage, ['reasoning']) || 0)\n      + (numericField(usage.cache, ['read']) || 0)\n      + (numericField(usage.cache, ['write']) || 0);\n  }\n  const input = numericField(usage, ['inputTokens', 'input_tokens', 'promptTokens', 'prompt_tokens']) || 0;\n  const output = numericField(usage, ['outputTokens', 'output_tokens', 'completionTokens', 'completion_tokens']) || 0;\n  return input + output;\n}\n\nfunction secondsFromUsage(usage) {\n  if (!usage || typeof usage !== 'object') return 0;\n  const direct = numericField(usage, ['timeSeconds', 'time_seconds', 'seconds', 'durationSeconds', 'duration_seconds']);\n  if (direct !== null) return direct;\n  const millis = numericField(usage, ['timeMs', 'time_ms', 'durationMs', 'duration_ms']);\n  return millis === null ? 0 : Math.max(1, Math.trunc(millis / 1000));\n}\n\nfunction extractUsageFromEvent(event) {\n  const payload = eventPayloadFrom(event);\n  const properties = eventPropertiesFrom(payload);\n  const candidates = [\n    payload?.usage,\n    payload?.message?.usage,\n    properties.usage,\n    properties.info?.usage,\n    properties.info?.tokens,\n    properties.message?.usage,\n    properties.part?.usage,\n  ].filter((candidate) => candidate && typeof candidate === 'object');\n  const usage = candidates.find((candidate) => tokenCountFromUsage(candidate) > 0) || candidates[0] || null;\n  const tokenDelta = tokenCountFromUsage(usage);\n  const timeDeltaSeconds = secondsFromUsage(usage);\n  const nativeUsage = usage === properties.info?.tokens;\n  const source = sanitizeInlineText(\n    usage?.source || usage?.usageSource || (nativeUsage ? 'opencode-native-tokens' : tokenDelta > 0 ? 'message.updated' : 'unavailable'),\n    80,\n  );\n  return {\n    tokenDelta,\n    timeDeltaSeconds,\n    usageSource: source || 'unavailable',\n  };\n}\n\nfunction extractErrorFromEvent(event) {\n  const payload = eventPayloadFrom(event);\n  const properties = eventPropertiesFrom(payload);\n  return [\n    payload?.error,\n    payload?.message?.error,\n    properties.error,\n    properties.info?.error,\n    properties.message?.error,\n    properties.part?.error,\n  ].find((candidate) => candidate && typeof candidate === 'object') || null;\n}\n\nfunction firstValue(source, keys) {\n  if (!source || typeof source !== 'object') return undefined;\n  for (const key of keys) {\n    if (source[key] !== undefined) return source[key];\n  }\n  return undefined;\n}\n\nfunction statusCodeFromError(error) {\n  const candidates = [\n    error?.statusCode,\n    error?.status,\n    error?.code,\n    error?.data?.statusCode,\n    error?.data?.status,\n    error?.response?.statusCode,\n    error?.response?.status,\n  ];\n  for (const candidate of candidates) {\n    const numeric = Number(candidate);\n    if (Number.isFinite(numeric)) return Math.trunc(numeric);\n  }\n  return null;\n}\n\nfunction errorMessageText(error) {\n  return [\n    error?.message,\n    error?.data?.message,\n    error?.data?.error,\n    error?.body?.message,\n    error?.response?.message,\n  ].map((entry) => (entry === null || entry === undefined ? '' : String(entry))).filter(Boolean).join(' ');\n}\n\nfunction isProviderUsageLimit(error) {\n  if (!error || typeof error !== 'object') return false;\n  if (statusCodeFromError(error) === 429) return true;\n  return /\\b(?:rate\\s*limit(?:ed)?|too many requests|usage[_ -]?limit(?:ed)?|insufficient quota|quota (?:exceeded|limit|reached))\\b/i.test(errorMessageText(error));\n}\n\nfunction retryAfterDeadlineFromValue(value, unit, rawOptions = {}) {\n  if (value === null || value === undefined || value === '') return null;\n  const timestamp = nowMs(rawOptions);\n  const numeric = Number(value);\n  if (Number.isFinite(numeric) && numeric > 0) {\n    const normalizedUnit = sanitizeInlineText(unit || '', 20).toLowerCase();\n    if (unit === 'ms') return Math.trunc(timestamp + numeric);\n    if (normalizedUnit === 'ms' || normalizedUnit === 'millisecond' || normalizedUnit === 'milliseconds') {\n      return Math.trunc(timestamp + numeric);\n    }\n    if (normalizedUnit === 's' || normalizedUnit === 'sec' || normalizedUnit === 'second' || normalizedUnit === 'seconds') {\n      return Math.trunc(timestamp + (numeric * 1000));\n    }\n    if (numeric > 1000000000000) return Math.trunc(numeric);\n    return Math.trunc(timestamp + (numeric * 1000));\n  }\n  const dateMs = Date.parse(String(value));\n  return Number.isFinite(dateMs) && dateMs > timestamp ? Math.trunc(dateMs) : null;\n}\n\nfunction providerRetryAfterDeadlineMs(error, rawOptions = {}) {\n  const headerRetryAfter = firstValue(error?.headers, ['retry-after', 'Retry-After'])\n    ?? firstValue(error?.data?.headers, ['retry-after', 'Retry-After'])\n    ?? firstValue(error?.response?.headers, ['retry-after', 'Retry-After']);\n  const candidates = [\n    [error?.retryAfterMs, 'ms'],\n    [error?.data?.retryAfterMs, 'ms'],\n    [error?.retryAfter, 'seconds'],\n    [error?.retry_after, 'seconds'],\n    [error?.data?.retryAfter, 'seconds'],\n    [error?.data?.retry_after, 'seconds'],\n    [headerRetryAfter, 'seconds'],\n  ];\n  for (const [value, unit] of candidates) {\n    const deadline = retryAfterDeadlineFromValue(value, unit, rawOptions);\n    if (deadline !== null) return deadline;\n  }\n  return null;\n}\n\nfunction providerUsageLimitPatch(error, rawOptions = {}) {\n  return {\n    status: 'usage_limited',\n    continuationSuppressed: true,\n    continuationSuppressedReason: 'usage_limited',\n    providerRetryAfterMs: providerRetryAfterDeadlineMs(error, rawOptions),\n  };\n}\n\nfunction roleFromObject(value) {\n  if (!value || typeof value !== 'object') return null;\n  return sanitizeInlineText(value.role || value.author?.role || value.sender?.role || '', 80).toLowerCase() || null;\n}\n\nfunction textFromValue(value, depth = 0) {\n  if (depth > 4 || value === null || value === undefined) return '';\n  if (typeof value === 'string') return value;\n  if (Array.isArray(value)) return value.map((entry) => textFromValue(entry, depth + 1)).filter(Boolean).join(' ');\n  if (typeof value !== 'object') return '';\n  for (const key of ['text', 'content', 'markdown', 'output', 'summary']) {\n    const text = textFromValue(value[key], depth + 1);\n    if (text) return text;\n  }\n  return '';\n}\n\nfunction extractAssistantEvidence(event, rawOptions = {}) {\n  const options = normalizeOptions(rawOptions);\n  const payload = eventPayloadFrom(event);\n  const properties = eventPropertiesFrom(payload);\n  const candidates = [\n    payload?.message,\n    payload?.info,\n    payload?.part,\n    properties.message,\n    properties.info,\n    properties.part,\n    payload,\n  ].filter((candidate) => candidate && typeof candidate === 'object');\n  const role = candidates.map(roleFromObject).find(Boolean);\n  if (role && role !== 'assistant') return null;\n  const text = candidates.map((candidate) => textFromValue(candidate)).find(Boolean);\n  const redacted = redactEvidence(text, options.maxEvidenceChars);\n  return redacted || null;\n}\n\nfunction extractAssistantTextPartEvidence(event, rawOptions = {}) {\n  const payload = eventPayloadFrom(event);\n  const properties = eventPropertiesFrom(payload);\n  const part = payload?.part || properties.part;\n  if (!part || part.type !== 'text') return null;\n  const role = [part, payload?.info, properties.info, payload].map(roleFromObject).find(Boolean);\n  if (role !== 'assistant') return null;\n  return extractAssistantEvidence(event, rawOptions);\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 5. STATE STORE\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * Ensure the goal state directory exists.\n *\n * @param {Object} [rawOptions] - State helper options\n * @param {string} [rawOptions.stateDir] - Override directory for tests\n * @returns {Promise<string>} Absolute state directory path\n */\nasync function ensureGoalStateDir(rawOptions = {}) {\n  const options = normalizeOptions(rawOptions);\n  if (knownStateDirs.has(options.stateDir)) return options.stateDir;\n  countMetric(options, 'mkdirStateDir');\n  await mkdir(options.stateDir, { recursive: true, mode: 0o700 });\n  knownStateDirs.add(options.stateDir);\n  return options.stateDir;\n}\n\nasync function ensureGoalArchiveDir(rawOptions = {}) {\n  const stateDir = await ensureGoalStateDir(rawOptions);\n  const archiveDir = join(stateDir, '.archive');\n  countMetric(rawOptions, 'mkdirArchiveDir');\n  await mkdir(archiveDir, { recursive: true, mode: 0o700 });\n  return archiveDir;\n}\n\n/**\n * Resolve a per-session goal state file path.\n *\n * @param {string} sessionID - OpenCode session id","lineStart":760,"lineEnd":1119,"totalLines":2986,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/plugins/mk-goal.js","time":{"start":1783744396385,"end":1783744396389}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b473eae8e75e964016a51c78c09448191b6ccd11b2ee2a26a"}},"id":"prt_f4f737c56001dVqFR9mop9uq3z","sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","messageID":"msg_f4f7346bd001QRNhgBYqYi0PtE"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783744396402,"sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ddVU1W9CLBEWdGd1Q3UttW3b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/plugins/mk-spec-memory.js","offset":1,"limit":360},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/plugins/mk-spec-memory.js</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n2: // ║ COMPONENT: Spec Memory OpenCode Plugin (mk-spec-memory)                 ║\n3: // ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n4: // ║ PURPOSE: Inject Spec Kit continuity into OpenCode model context and     ║\n5: // ║          expose warm bridge status without leaking local paths.          ║\n6: // ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n7: 'use strict';\n8: \n9: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n10: // 1. IMPORTS\n11: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n12: \n13: import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n14: import { spawn } from 'node:child_process';\n15: import { statSync } from 'node:fs';\n16: import { readFile } from 'node:fs/promises';\n17: import { homedir } from 'node:os';\n18: import { join, resolve as resolvePath } from 'node:path';\n19: import { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';\n20: \n21: import { tool } from '@opencode-ai/plugin/tool';\n22: \n23: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n24: // 2. CONSTANTS\n25: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n26: \n27: const PLUGIN_ID = 'mk-spec-memory';\n28: const DEFAULT_CACHE_TTL_MS = 5000;\n29: const DEFAULT_BRIDGE_TIMEOUT_MS = 3000;\n30: const DEFAULT_CLI_TIMEOUT_MS = 2500;\n31: const DEFAULT_NODE_BINARY = 'node';\n32: const DEFAULT_MAX_BRIEF_CHARS = 2400;\n33: const DEFAULT_MAX_CACHE_ENTRIES = 200;\n34: const MAX_BRIDGE_STDOUT_BYTES = 1024 * 1024;\n35: const BRIEF_MARKER_PREFIX = '[mk-spec-memory:continuity:';\n36: const BRIEF_MARKER_DIGEST_CHARS = 16;\n37: const MIN_MAX_BRIEF_CHARS = BRIEF_MARKER_PREFIX.length + BRIEF_MARKER_DIGEST_CHARS + 1;\n38: const DISABLED_ENV = 'MK_SPEC_MEMORY_PLUGIN_DISABLED';\n39: const LEGACY_DISABLED_ENV = 'SPECKIT_SPEC_MEMORY_PLUGIN_DISABLED';\n40: const BRIDGE_PATH = fileURLToPath(new URL('../skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/plugin_bridges/mk-spec-memory-bridge.mjs', import.meta.url));\n41: const SOURCE_PATHS = [\n42:   BRIDGE_PATH,\n43:   fileURLToPath(new URL('../bin/spec-memory.cjs', import.meta.url)),\n44: ];\n45: \n46: async function loadConfig() {\n47:   const path = join(homedir(), '.config', 'opencode', 'plugin', 'mk-spec-memory.json');\n48:   let raw;\n49:   try {\n50:     raw = await readFile(path, 'utf-8');\n51:   } catch (error) {\n52:     const errorCode = typeof error?.code === 'string' ? error.code : 'UNKNOWN';\n53:     return {\n54:       config: {},\n55:       status: errorCode === 'ENOENT' ? 'missing' : 'read_error',\n56:       errorCode: errorCode === 'ENOENT' ? null : errorCode,\n57:     };\n58:   }\n59: \n60:   try {\n61:     const parsed = JSON.parse(raw);\n62:     if (!parsed || typeof parsed !== 'object' || Array.isArray(parsed)) {\n63:       return { config: {}, status: 'parse_error', errorCode: 'INVALID_SHAPE' };\n64:     }\n65:     return { config: parsed, status: 'loaded', errorCode: null };\n66:   } catch {\n67:     return { config: {}, status: 'parse_error', errorCode: 'INVALID_JSON' };\n68:   }\n69: }\n70: \n71: const configPromise = loadConfig();\n72: \n73: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n74: // 3. PURE UTILITIES\n75: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n76: \n77: function normalizePositiveInt(value, fallback) {\n78:   return Number.isFinite(value) && value > 0 ? Math.trunc(value) : fallback;\n79: }\n80: \n81: function envDisablesPlugin() {\n82:   return process.env[DISABLED_ENV] === '1' || process.env[LEGACY_DISABLED_ENV] === '1';\n83: }\n84: \n85: function disabledEnvName() {\n86:   if (process.env[DISABLED_ENV] === '1') return DISABLED_ENV;\n87:   if (process.env[LEGACY_DISABLED_ENV] === '1') return LEGACY_DISABLED_ENV;\n88:   return null;\n89: }\n90: \n91: function normalizeOptions(rawOptions) {\n92:   const options = rawOptions && typeof rawOptions === 'object' ? rawOptions : {};\n93:   const envCacheTtlMs = Number(process.env.MK_SPEC_MEMORY_CACHE_TTL_MS);\n94:   const envBridgeTimeoutMs = Number(process.env.MK_SPEC_MEMORY_BRIDGE_TIMEOUT_MS);\n95:   const envCliTimeoutMs = Number(process.env.MK_SPEC_MEMORY_CLI_TIMEOUT_MS);\n96:   const envMaxBriefChars = Number(process.env.MK_SPEC_MEMORY_MAX_BRIEF_CHARS);\n97:   const envMaxCacheEntries = Number(process.env.MK_SPEC_MEMORY_MAX_CACHE_ENTRIES);\n98: \n99:   return {\n100:     enabled: options.enabled !== false && !envDisablesPlugin(),\n101:     cacheTtlMs: normalizePositiveInt(options.cacheTtlMs ?? options.cacheTTLMs, normalizePositiveInt(envCacheTtlMs, DEFAULT_CACHE_TTL_MS)),\n102:     bridgeTimeoutMs: normalizePositiveInt(options.bridgeTimeoutMs, normalizePositiveInt(envBridgeTimeoutMs, DEFAULT_BRIDGE_TIMEOUT_MS)),\n103:     cliTimeoutMs: normalizePositiveInt(options.cliTimeoutMs, normalizePositiveInt(envCliTimeoutMs, DEFAULT_CLI_TIMEOUT_MS)),\n104:     nodeBinary: typeof options.nodeBinaryOverride === 'string' && options.nodeBinaryOverride.trim()\n105:       ? options.nodeBinaryOverride.trim()\n106:       : (process.env.MK_SPEC_MEMORY_NODE_BINARY || process.env.SPEC_KIT_PLUGIN_NODE_BINARY || DEFAULT_NODE_BINARY),\n107:     specFolder: typeof options.specFolder === 'string' && options.specFolder.trim()\n108:       ? options.specFolder.trim()\n109:       : (process.env.MK_SPEC_MEMORY_SPEC_FOLDER || undefined),\n110:     maxBriefChars: Math.max(\n111:       MIN_MAX_BRIEF_CHARS,\n112:       normalizePositiveInt(options.maxBriefChars, normalizePositiveInt(envMaxBriefChars, DEFAULT_MAX_BRIEF_CHARS)),\n113:     ),\n114:     maxCacheEntries: normalizePositiveInt(options.maxCacheEntries, normalizePositiveInt(envMaxCacheEntries, DEFAULT_MAX_CACHE_ENTRIES)),\n115:     sourceSignatureOverride: typeof options.sourceSignatureOverride === 'string' ? options.sourceSignatureOverride : null,\n116:   };\n117: }\n118: \n119: function sourceSignature() {\n120:   const hash = createHash('sha256');\n121:   for (const sourcePath of SOURCE_PATHS) {\n122:     try {\n123:       const stat = statSync(sourcePath);\n124:       hash.update(sourcePath);\n125:       hash.update('\\u001f');\n126:       hash.update(String(stat.mtimeMs));\n127:       hash.update('\\u001f');\n128:       hash.update(String(stat.size));\n129:       hash.update('\\u001e');\n130:     } catch {\n131:       hash.update(sourcePath);\n132:       hash.update('\\u001fmissing\\u001e');\n133:     }\n134:   }\n135:   return hash.digest('hex');\n136: }\n137: \n138: function stableStringify(value) {\n139:   if (!value || typeof value !== 'object') return JSON.stringify(String(value));\n140:   if (Array.isArray(value)) return `[${value.map((entry) => stableStringify(entry)).join(',')}]`;\n141:   return `{${Object.keys(value).sort().map((key) => `${JSON.stringify(key)}:${stableStringify(value[key])}`).join(',')}}`;\n142: }\n143: \n144: function normalizeSessionID(value) {\n145:   if (value === null || value === undefined || value === '') return '__global__';\n146:   if (typeof value === 'object') return stableStringify(value);\n147:   return String(value);\n148: }\n149: \n150: function sessionIdFrom(input) {\n151:   if (!input || typeof input !== 'object') return '__global__';\n152:   return normalizeSessionID(\n153:     input.sessionID\n154:     || input.sessionId\n155:     || input.session?.id\n156:     || input.properties?.sessionID\n157:     || input.properties?.info?.sessionID\n158:     || input.properties?.info?.id\n159:     || '__global__',\n160:   );\n161: }\n162: \n163: function eventPayloadFrom(event) {\n164:   if (event?.payload && typeof event.payload === 'object') return event.payload;\n165:   return event;\n166: }\n167: \n168: function eventTypeFrom(event) {\n169:   const payload = eventPayloadFrom(event);\n170:   return typeof payload?.type === 'string' ? payload.type : null;\n171: }\n172: \n173: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n174: // 4. EVENT HELPERS\n175: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n176: \n177: function extractEventSessionID(event) {\n178:   const payload = eventPayloadFrom(event);\n179:   return sessionIdFrom(payload);\n180: }\n181: \n182: function normalizeWorkspaceRoot(workspaceRoot) {\n183:   if (typeof workspaceRoot === 'string' && workspaceRoot.trim()) {\n184:     return resolvePath(workspaceRoot.trim());\n185:   }\n186:   return resolvePath(process.cwd());\n187: }\n188: \n189: function statusSafeBinary(binary) {\n190:   if (typeof binary === 'string' && (binary.includes('/') || binary.includes('\\\\'))) {\n191:     return '[configured-node]';\n192:   }\n193:   return binary;\n194: }\n195: \n196: function parseBridgeResponse(stdout) {\n197:   if (!stdout.trim()) {\n198:     return { status: 'fail_open', brief: null, data: null, metadata: {}, error: 'EMPTY_STDOUT' };\n199:   }\n200:   try {\n201:     const parsed = JSON.parse(stdout.trim());\n202:     const status = ['ok', 'skipped', 'fail_open'].includes(parsed?.status) ? parsed.status : 'fail_open';\n203:     return {\n204:       status,\n205:       brief: typeof parsed?.brief === 'string' && parsed.brief.trim() ? parsed.brief : null,\n206:       data: parsed?.data ?? null,\n207:       metadata: parsed?.metadata && typeof parsed.metadata === 'object' ? parsed.metadata : {},\n208:       ...(typeof parsed?.error === 'string' ? { error: parsed.error } : {}),\n209:     };\n210:   } catch {\n211:     return { status: 'fail_open', brief: null, data: null, metadata: {}, error: 'PARSE_FAIL' };\n212:   }\n213: }\n214: \n215: function cacheKeyFor({ sessionID, specFolder, workspaceRoot, signature }) {\n216:   const sessionKey = normalizeSessionID(sessionID);\n217:   const payloadKey = createHash('sha256')\n218:     .update(normalizeSessionID(sessionID))\n219:     .update('\\u001f')\n220:     .update(specFolder ?? '__workspace__')\n221:     .update('\\u001f')\n222:     .update(workspaceRoot)\n223:     .update('\\u001f')\n224:     .update(signature)\n225:     .digest('hex');\n226:   return `${sessionKey}::${payloadKey}`;\n227: }\n228: \n229: function insertWithEviction(cache, key, value, maxEntries) {\n230:   cache.set(key, value);\n231:   while (cache.size > maxEntries) {\n232:     const oldest = cache.keys().next().value;\n233:     cache.delete(oldest);\n234:   }\n235: }\n236: \n237: function clampBrief(brief, maxChars) {\n238:   if (typeof brief !== 'string' || brief.length <= maxChars) return brief;\n239:   if (maxChars <= 3) return '.'.repeat(Math.max(0, maxChars));\n240:   return `${brief.slice(0, maxChars - 3).trimEnd()}...`;\n241: }\n242: \n243: function markedBrief(brief, maxChars) {\n244:   const digest = createHash('sha256')\n245:     .update(brief)\n246:     .digest('hex')\n247:     .slice(0, BRIEF_MARKER_DIGEST_CHARS);\n248:   const marker = `${BRIEF_MARKER_PREFIX}${digest}]`;\n249:   const contentBudget = Math.max(0, maxChars - marker.length - 1);\n250:   const content = contentBudget > 0 ? clampBrief(brief, contentBudget) : '';\n251:   return {\n252:     marker,\n253:     text: content ? `${content}\\n${marker}` : marker,\n254:   };\n255: }\n256: \n257: function bridgePayload({ request, projectDir, sessionID, options }) {\n258:   const payload = {\n259:     request,\n260:     workspaceRoot: projectDir,\n261:     timeoutMs: options.cliTimeoutMs,\n262:     maxBriefChars: options.maxBriefChars,\n263:     specFolder: options.specFolder,\n264:     sessionId: normalizeSessionID(sessionID) === '__global__' ? undefined : normalizeSessionID(sessionID),\n265:   };\n266:   return JSON.stringify(payload);\n267: }\n268: \n269: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n270: // 5. PLUGIN FACTORY\n271: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n272: \n273: /**\n274:  * Create the Spec Kit memory OpenCode plugin hooks.\n275:  *\n276:  * @param {import('@opencode-ai/plugin').PluginInput} ctx - OpenCode plugin context\n277:  * @param {Object} [rawOptions] - Plugin options\n278:  * @param {boolean} [rawOptions.enabled] - Whether continuity injection is enabled\n279:  * @param {number} [rawOptions.cacheTtlMs] - Continuity cache TTL in milliseconds\n280:  * @param {number} [rawOptions.cacheTTLMs] - Continuity cache TTL alias in milliseconds\n281:  * @param {number} [rawOptions.bridgeTimeoutMs] - Bridge subprocess timeout in milliseconds\n282:  * @param {number} [rawOptions.cliTimeoutMs] - Warm CLI timeout passed to the bridge\n283:  * @param {string} [rawOptions.nodeBinaryOverride] - Node binary used for the bridge subprocess\n284:  * @param {string} [rawOptions.specFolder] - Optional spec folder scope for continuity recovery\n285:  * @param {number} [rawOptions.maxBriefChars] - Maximum injected continuity brief characters\n286:  * @param {number} [rawOptions.maxCacheEntries] - Maximum continuity cache entries\n287:  * @param {string} [rawOptions.sourceSignatureOverride] - Test override for source signature\n288:  * @returns {Promise<Object>} Hooks with `event`, `experimental.chat.system.transform`, and `tool`\n289:  */\n290: export default async function MkSpecMemoryPlugin(ctx, rawOptions) {\n291:   const configResult = await configPromise;\n292:   const merged = { ...configResult.config, ...rawOptions };\n293:   const options = normalizeOptions(merged);\n294:   const projectDir = normalizeWorkspaceRoot(ctx?.directory);\n295: \n296:   const state = {\n297:     continuityCache: new Map(),\n298:     inFlight: new Map(),\n299:     sessionGenerations: new Map(),\n300:     runtimeReady: false,\n301:     lastBridgeStatus: 'uninitialized',\n302:     lastErrorCode: null,\n303:     lastDurationMs: 0,\n304:     bridgeInvocations: 0,\n305:     cacheHits: 0,\n306:     cacheMisses: 0,\n307:     continuityLookups: 0,\n308:     disabledReason: !options.enabled ? (disabledEnvName() ?? 'config_enabled_false') : null,\n309:   };\n310: \n311:   function runBridge({ request, sessionID }) {\n312:     const startedAt = Date.now();\n313:     state.bridgeInvocations += 1;\n314:     return new Promise((resolve) => {\n315:       const child = spawn(options.nodeBinary, [BRIDGE_PATH], {\n316:         cwd: projectDir,\n317:         env: process.env,\n318:         stdio: ['pipe', 'pipe', 'pipe'],\n319:       });\n320:       const stdoutChunks = [];\n321:       let stdoutBytes = 0;\n322:       let settled = false;\n323:       let timeout;\n324:       const finish = (response) => {\n325:         if (settled) return;\n326:         settled = true;\n327:         if (timeout) clearTimeout(timeout);\n328:         state.lastBridgeStatus = response.status;\n329:         state.lastErrorCode = response.error ?? null;\n330:         state.lastDurationMs = Date.now() - startedAt;\n331:         state.runtimeReady = response.status === 'ok';\n332:         resolve(response);\n333:       };\n334:       timeout = setTimeout(() => {\n335:         if (settled) return;\n336:         child.kill('SIGTERM');\n337:         const forceKill = setTimeout(() => child.kill('SIGKILL'), 1000);\n338:         forceKill.unref?.();\n339:         finish({ status: 'fail_open', brief: null, data: null, metadata: {}, error: 'TIMEOUT' });\n340:       }, options.bridgeTimeoutMs);\n341: \n342:       child.stdout?.on('data', (chunk) => {\n343:         if (settled) return;\n344:         const buffer = Buffer.isBuffer(chunk) ? chunk : Buffer.from(String(chunk));\n345:         if (stdoutBytes + buffer.length > MAX_BRIDGE_STDOUT_BYTES) {\n346:           child.kill('SIGKILL');\n347:           finish({ status: 'fail_open', brief: null, data: null, metadata: {}, error: 'STDOUT_OVERFLOW' });\n348:           return;\n349:         }\n350:         stdoutChunks.push(buffer);\n351:         stdoutBytes += buffer.length;\n352:       });\n353:       child.stderr?.on('data', () => {});\n354:       child.on('error', () => {\n355:         finish({ status: 'fail_open', brief: null, data: null, metadata: {}, error: 'SPAWN_ERROR' });\n356:       });\n357:       child.on('close', (code) => {\n358:         if (settled) return;\n359:         const response = parseBridgeResponse(Buffer.concat(stdoutChunks, stdoutBytes).toString('utf8'));\n360:         if (code !== 0 && response.status !== 'fail_open') {\n\n(Showing lines 1-360 of 551. Use offset=361 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ COMPONENT: Spec Memory OpenCode Plugin (mk-spec-memory)                 ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ PURPOSE: Inject Spec Kit continuity into OpenCode model context and     ║\n// ║          expose warm bridge status without leaking local paths.          ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n'use strict';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. IMPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nimport { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\nimport { spawn } from 'node:child_process';\nimport { statSync } from 'node:fs';\nimport { readFile } from 'node:fs/promises';\nimport { homedir } from 'node:os';\nimport { join, resolve as resolvePath } from 'node:path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/plugins/mk-spec-memory.js","text":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ COMPONENT: Spec Memory OpenCode Plugin (mk-spec-memory)                 ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ PURPOSE: Inject Spec Kit continuity into OpenCode model context and     ║\n// ║          expose warm bridge status without leaking local paths.          ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n'use strict';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. IMPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nimport { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\nimport { spawn } from 'node:child_process';\nimport { statSync } from 'node:fs';\nimport { readFile } from 'node:fs/promises';\nimport { homedir } from 'node:os';\nimport { join, resolve as resolvePath } from 'node:path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';\n\nimport { tool } from '@opencode-ai/plugin/tool';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 2. CONSTANTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst PLUGIN_ID = 'mk-spec-memory';\nconst DEFAULT_CACHE_TTL_MS = 5000;\nconst DEFAULT_BRIDGE_TIMEOUT_MS = 3000;\nconst DEFAULT_CLI_TIMEOUT_MS = 2500;\nconst DEFAULT_NODE_BINARY = 'node';\nconst DEFAULT_MAX_BRIEF_CHARS = 2400;\nconst DEFAULT_MAX_CACHE_ENTRIES = 200;\nconst MAX_BRIDGE_STDOUT_BYTES = 1024 * 1024;\nconst BRIEF_MARKER_PREFIX = '[mk-spec-memory:continuity:';\nconst BRIEF_MARKER_DIGEST_CHARS = 16;\nconst MIN_MAX_BRIEF_CHARS = BRIEF_MARKER_PREFIX.length + BRIEF_MARKER_DIGEST_CHARS + 1;\nconst DISABLED_ENV = 'MK_SPEC_MEMORY_PLUGIN_DISABLED';\nconst LEGACY_DISABLED_ENV = 'SPECKIT_SPEC_MEMORY_PLUGIN_DISABLED';\nconst BRIDGE_PATH = fileURLToPath(new URL('../skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/plugin_bridges/mk-spec-memory-bridge.mjs', import.meta.url));\nconst SOURCE_PATHS = [\n  BRIDGE_PATH,\n  fileURLToPath(new URL('../bin/spec-memory.cjs', import.meta.url)),\n];\n\nasync function loadConfig() {\n  const path = join(homedir(), '.config', 'opencode', 'plugin', 'mk-spec-memory.json');\n  let raw;\n  try {\n    raw = await readFile(path, 'utf-8');\n  } catch (error) {\n    const errorCode = typeof error?.code === 'string' ? error.code : 'UNKNOWN';\n    return {\n      config: {},\n      status: errorCode === 'ENOENT' ? 'missing' : 'read_error',\n      errorCode: errorCode === 'ENOENT' ? null : errorCode,\n    };\n  }\n\n  try {\n    const parsed = JSON.parse(raw);\n    if (!parsed || typeof parsed !== 'object' || Array.isArray(parsed)) {\n      return { config: {}, status: 'parse_error', errorCode: 'INVALID_SHAPE' };\n    }\n    return { config: parsed, status: 'loaded', errorCode: null };\n  } catch {\n    return { config: {}, status: 'parse_error', errorCode: 'INVALID_JSON' };\n  }\n}\n\nconst configPromise = loadConfig();\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 3. PURE UTILITIES\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunction normalizePositiveInt(value, fallback) {\n  return Number.isFinite(value) && value > 0 ? Math.trunc(value) : fallback;\n}\n\nfunction envDisablesPlugin() {\n  return process.env[DISABLED_ENV] === '1' || process.env[LEGACY_DISABLED_ENV] === '1';\n}\n\nfunction disabledEnvName() {\n  if (process.env[DISABLED_ENV] === '1') return DISABLED_ENV;\n  if (process.env[LEGACY_DISABLED_ENV] === '1') return LEGACY_DISABLED_ENV;\n  return null;\n}\n\nfunction normalizeOptions(rawOptions) {\n  const options = rawOptions && typeof rawOptions === 'object' ? rawOptions : {};\n  const envCacheTtlMs = Number(process.env.MK_SPEC_MEMORY_CACHE_TTL_MS);\n  const envBridgeTimeoutMs = Number(process.env.MK_SPEC_MEMORY_BRIDGE_TIMEOUT_MS);\n  const envCliTimeoutMs = Number(process.env.MK_SPEC_MEMORY_CLI_TIMEOUT_MS);\n  const envMaxBriefChars = Number(process.env.MK_SPEC_MEMORY_MAX_BRIEF_CHARS);\n  const envMaxCacheEntries = Number(process.env.MK_SPEC_MEMORY_MAX_CACHE_ENTRIES);\n\n  return {\n    enabled: options.enabled !== false && !envDisablesPlugin(),\n    cacheTtlMs: normalizePositiveInt(options.cacheTtlMs ?? options.cacheTTLMs, normalizePositiveInt(envCacheTtlMs, DEFAULT_CACHE_TTL_MS)),\n    bridgeTimeoutMs: normalizePositiveInt(options.bridgeTimeoutMs, normalizePositiveInt(envBridgeTimeoutMs, DEFAULT_BRIDGE_TIMEOUT_MS)),\n    cliTimeoutMs: normalizePositiveInt(options.cliTimeoutMs, normalizePositiveInt(envCliTimeoutMs, DEFAULT_CLI_TIMEOUT_MS)),\n    nodeBinary: typeof options.nodeBinaryOverride === 'string' && options.nodeBinaryOverride.trim()\n      ? options.nodeBinaryOverride.trim()\n      : (process.env.MK_SPEC_MEMORY_NODE_BINARY || process.env.SPEC_KIT_PLUGIN_NODE_BINARY || DEFAULT_NODE_BINARY),\n    specFolder: typeof options.specFolder === 'string' && options.specFolder.trim()\n      ? options.specFolder.trim()\n      : (process.env.MK_SPEC_MEMORY_SPEC_FOLDER || undefined),\n    maxBriefChars: Math.max(\n      MIN_MAX_BRIEF_CHARS,\n      normalizePositiveInt(options.maxBriefChars, normalizePositiveInt(envMaxBriefChars, DEFAULT_MAX_BRIEF_CHARS)),\n    ),\n    maxCacheEntries: normalizePositiveInt(options.maxCacheEntries, normalizePositiveInt(envMaxCacheEntries, DEFAULT_MAX_CACHE_ENTRIES)),\n    sourceSignatureOverride: typeof options.sourceSignatureOverride === 'string' ? options.sourceSignatureOverride : null,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction sourceSignature() {\n  const hash = createHash('sha256');\n  for (const sourcePath of SOURCE_PATHS) {\n    try {\n      const stat = statSync(sourcePath);\n      hash.update(sourcePath);\n      hash.update('\\u001f');\n      hash.update(String(stat.mtimeMs));\n      hash.update('\\u001f');\n      hash.update(String(stat.size));\n      hash.update('\\u001e');\n    } catch {\n      hash.update(sourcePath);\n      hash.update('\\u001fmissing\\u001e');\n    }\n  }\n  return hash.digest('hex');\n}\n\nfunction stableStringify(value) {\n  if (!value || typeof value !== 'object') return JSON.stringify(String(value));\n  if (Array.isArray(value)) return `[${value.map((entry) => stableStringify(entry)).join(',')}]`;\n  return `{${Object.keys(value).sort().map((key) => `${JSON.stringify(key)}:${stableStringify(value[key])}`).join(',')}}`;\n}\n\nfunction normalizeSessionID(value) {\n  if (value === null || value === undefined || value === '') return '__global__';\n  if (typeof value === 'object') return stableStringify(value);\n  return String(value);\n}\n\nfunction sessionIdFrom(input) {\n  if (!input || typeof input !== 'object') return '__global__';\n  return normalizeSessionID(\n    input.sessionID\n    || input.sessionId\n    || input.session?.id\n    || input.properties?.sessionID\n    || input.properties?.info?.sessionID\n    || input.properties?.info?.id\n    || '__global__',\n  );\n}\n\nfunction eventPayloadFrom(event) {\n  if (event?.payload && typeof event.payload === 'object') return event.payload;\n  return event;\n}\n\nfunction eventTypeFrom(event) {\n  const payload = eventPayloadFrom(event);\n  return typeof payload?.type === 'string' ? payload.type : null;\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 4. EVENT HELPERS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunction extractEventSessionID(event) {\n  const payload = eventPayloadFrom(event);\n  return sessionIdFrom(payload);\n}\n\nfunction normalizeWorkspaceRoot(workspaceRoot) {\n  if (typeof workspaceRoot === 'string' && workspaceRoot.trim()) {\n    return resolvePath(workspaceRoot.trim());\n  }\n  return resolvePath(process.cwd());\n}\n\nfunction statusSafeBinary(binary) {\n  if (typeof binary === 'string' && (binary.includes('/') || binary.includes('\\\\'))) {\n    return '[configured-node]';\n  }\n  return binary;\n}\n\nfunction parseBridgeResponse(stdout) {\n  if (!stdout.trim()) {\n    return { status: 'fail_open', brief: null, data: null, metadata: {}, error: 'EMPTY_STDOUT' };\n  }\n  try {\n    const parsed = JSON.parse(stdout.trim());\n    const status = ['ok', 'skipped', 'fail_open'].includes(parsed?.status) ? parsed.status : 'fail_open';\n    return {\n      status,\n      brief: typeof parsed?.brief === 'string' && parsed.brief.trim() ? parsed.brief : null,\n      data: parsed?.data ?? null,\n      metadata: parsed?.metadata && typeof parsed.metadata === 'object' ? parsed.metadata : {},\n      ...(typeof parsed?.error === 'string' ? { error: parsed.error } : {}),\n    };\n  } catch {\n    return { status: 'fail_open', brief: null, data: null, metadata: {}, error: 'PARSE_FAIL' };\n  }\n}\n\nfunction cacheKeyFor({ sessionID, specFolder, workspaceRoot, signature }) {\n  const sessionKey = normalizeSessionID(sessionID);\n  const payloadKey = createHash('sha256')\n    .update(normalizeSessionID(sessionID))\n    .update('\\u001f')\n    .update(specFolder ?? '__workspace__')\n    .update('\\u001f')\n    .update(workspaceRoot)\n    .update('\\u001f')\n    .update(signature)\n    .digest('hex');\n  return `${sessionKey}::${payloadKey}`;\n}\n\nfunction insertWithEviction(cache, key, value, maxEntries) {\n  cache.set(key, value);\n  while (cache.size > maxEntries) {\n    const oldest = cache.keys().next().value;\n    cache.delete(oldest);\n  }\n}\n\nfunction clampBrief(brief, maxChars) {\n  if (typeof brief !== 'string' || brief.length <= maxChars) return brief;\n  if (maxChars <= 3) return '.'.repeat(Math.max(0, maxChars));\n  return `${brief.slice(0, maxChars - 3).trimEnd()}...`;\n}\n\nfunction markedBrief(brief, maxChars) {\n  const digest = createHash('sha256')\n    .update(brief)\n    .digest('hex')\n    .slice(0, BRIEF_MARKER_DIGEST_CHARS);\n  const marker = `${BRIEF_MARKER_PREFIX}${digest}]`;\n  const contentBudget = Math.max(0, maxChars - marker.length - 1);\n  const content = contentBudget > 0 ? clampBrief(brief, contentBudget) : '';\n  return {\n    marker,\n    text: content ? `${content}\\n${marker}` : marker,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction bridgePayload({ request, projectDir, sessionID, options }) {\n  const payload = {\n    request,\n    workspaceRoot: projectDir,\n    timeoutMs: options.cliTimeoutMs,\n    maxBriefChars: options.maxBriefChars,\n    specFolder: options.specFolder,\n    sessionId: normalizeSessionID(sessionID) === '__global__' ? undefined : normalizeSessionID(sessionID),\n  };\n  return JSON.stringify(payload);\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 5. PLUGIN FACTORY\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * Create the Spec Kit memory OpenCode plugin hooks.\n *\n * @param {import('@opencode-ai/plugin').PluginInput} ctx - OpenCode plugin context\n * @param {Object} [rawOptions] - Plugin options\n * @param {boolean} [rawOptions.enabled] - Whether continuity injection is enabled\n * @param {number} [rawOptions.cacheTtlMs] - Continuity cache TTL in milliseconds\n * @param {number} [rawOptions.cacheTTLMs] - Continuity cache TTL alias in milliseconds\n * @param {number} [rawOptions.bridgeTimeoutMs] - Bridge subprocess timeout in milliseconds\n * @param {number} [rawOptions.cliTimeoutMs] - Warm CLI timeout passed to the bridge\n * @param {string} [rawOptions.nodeBinaryOverride] - Node binary used for the bridge subprocess\n * @param {string} [rawOptions.specFolder] - Optional spec folder scope for continuity recovery\n * @param {number} [rawOptions.maxBriefChars] - Maximum injected continuity brief characters\n * @param {number} [rawOptions.maxCacheEntries] - Maximum continuity cache entries\n * @param {string} [rawOptions.sourceSignatureOverride] - Test override for source signature\n * @returns {Promise<Object>} Hooks with `event`, `experimental.chat.system.transform`, and `tool`\n */\nexport default async function MkSpecMemoryPlugin(ctx, rawOptions) {\n  const configResult = await configPromise;\n  const merged = { ...configResult.config, ...rawOptions };\n  const options = normalizeOptions(merged);\n  const projectDir = normalizeWorkspaceRoot(ctx?.directory);\n\n  const state = {\n    continuityCache: new Map(),\n    inFlight: new Map(),\n    sessionGenerations: new Map(),\n    runtimeReady: false,\n    lastBridgeStatus: 'uninitialized',\n    lastErrorCode: null,\n    lastDurationMs: 0,\n    bridgeInvocations: 0,\n    cacheHits: 0,\n    cacheMisses: 0,\n    continuityLookups: 0,\n    disabledReason: !options.enabled ? (disabledEnvName() ?? 'config_enabled_false') : null,\n  };\n\n  function runBridge({ request, sessionID }) {\n    const startedAt = Date.now();\n    state.bridgeInvocations += 1;\n    return new Promise((resolve) => {\n      const child = spawn(options.nodeBinary, [BRIDGE_PATH], {\n        cwd: projectDir,\n        env: process.env,\n        stdio: ['pipe', 'pipe', 'pipe'],\n      });\n      const stdoutChunks = [];\n      let stdoutBytes = 0;\n      let settled = false;\n      let timeout;\n      const finish = (response) => {\n        if (settled) return;\n        settled = true;\n        if (timeout) clearTimeout(timeout);\n        state.lastBridgeStatus = response.status;\n        state.lastErrorCode = response.error ?? null;\n        state.lastDurationMs = Date.now() - startedAt;\n        state.runtimeReady = response.status === 'ok';\n        resolve(response);\n      };\n      timeout = setTimeout(() => {\n        if (settled) return;\n        child.kill('SIGTERM');\n        const forceKill = setTimeout(() => child.kill('SIGKILL'), 1000);\n        forceKill.unref?.();\n        finish({ status: 'fail_open', brief: null, data: null, metadata: {}, error: 'TIMEOUT' });\n      }, options.bridgeTimeoutMs);\n\n      child.stdout?.on('data', (chunk) => {\n        if (settled) return;\n        const buffer = Buffer.isBuffer(chunk) ? chunk : Buffer.from(String(chunk));\n        if (stdoutBytes + buffer.length > MAX_BRIDGE_STDOUT_BYTES) {\n          child.kill('SIGKILL');\n          finish({ status: 'fail_open', brief: null, data: null, metadata: {}, error: 'STDOUT_OVERFLOW' });\n          return;\n        }\n        stdoutChunks.push(buffer);\n        stdoutBytes += buffer.length;\n      });\n      child.stderr?.on('data', () => {});\n      child.on('error', () => {\n        finish({ status: 'fail_open', brief: null, data: null, metadata: {}, error: 'SPAWN_ERROR' });\n      });\n      child.on('close', (code) => {\n        if (settled) return;\n        const response = parseBridgeResponse(Buffer.concat(stdoutChunks, stdoutBytes).toString('utf8'));\n        if (code !== 0 && response.status !== 'fail_open') {","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":360,"totalLines":551,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/plugins/mk-spec-memory.js","time":{"start":1783744396396,"end":1783744396400}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b473eae8e75e964016a51c78c09488191a8e52ee225f8f965"}},"id":"prt_f4f737c640014eXEwWOkKzpwr9","sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","messageID":"msg_f4f7346bd001QRNhgBYqYi0PtE"}}
