{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783744412969,"sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_4kSttRYFBlFJLGlIsbIuoka1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"tool\\.execute\\.after","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public","include":"*.{js,ts,cjs,mjs,md}"},"output":"Found 39 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/glm52/deep-research-strategy.md:\n  Line 45: - `tool.execute.after` — Intercept tool call results after execution\n\n  Line 66: 3. **KQ-3**: Which OpenCode hook surfaces (`tool.execute.after`, `tool.register`, `event`) are currently underused and could host new value?\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/glm52/iterations/iteration-001.md:\n  Line 29: ### Candidate 2: Comment Hygiene PostToolUse Hook (sk-code → Claude PostToolUse/Write|Edit + OpenCode tool.execute.after)\n\n  Line 32: **Runtime surface:** Claude `PostToolUse` matcher `Write|Edit` + OpenCode `tool.execute.after`\n\n  Line 38: For OpenCode, a `tool.execute.after` plugin would serve the same role, inspecting the edited file path after a Write/Edit tool call completes.\n\n  Line 61: ### Candidate 4: Code-Graph Re-index Trigger (system-code-graph → OpenCode tool.execute.after + Claude PostToolUse/Write|Edit)\n\n  Line 64: **Runtime surface:** OpenCode `tool.execute.after` + Claude `PostToolUse/Write|Edit`\n\n  Line 66: The code graph is currently re-indexed manually via `code_graph_scan` or on SessionStart. After code edits, the graph goes stale until the next explicit scan. A `tool.execute.after` plugin (OpenCode) or `PostToolUse/Write|Edit` hook (Claude) could trigger an incremental re-index of just the edited file, keeping the graph fresh without a full rescan.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/glm52/iterations/iteration-002.md:\n  Line 9: ### Candidate 5: Frontmatter Version Validator Hook (sk-doc → Claude PostToolUse/Write|Edit + OpenCode tool.execute.after)\n\n  Line 12: **Runtime surface:** Claude `PostToolUse` matcher `Write|Edit` + OpenCode `tool.execute.after`\n\n  Line 69: ### Candidate 9: DQI Quality Score Live Feedback (sk-doc → OpenCode tool.execute.after)\n\n  Line 72: **Runtime surface:** OpenCode `tool.execute.after`\n\n  Line 76: A `tool.execute.after` plugin could run a lightweight DQI sub-check (placeholder detection, anchor integrity, section structure) on edited `.md` files under `specs/` or `.opencode/specs/` and surface a quality hint. This differs from Candidate 3 (spec validation) in that it scores documentation quality (DQI), not spec-folder structural validity.\n\n  Line 107: Inventory system-deep-loop (lifecycle hooks beyond dispatch guard), mcp-tooling/mcp-code-mode (tool registration hooks), and cli-external (dispatch preflight expansion). Also examine underused OpenCode surfaces (tool.execute.after, tool.register, event lifecycle).\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/129-opencode-plugins-hooks-remediation/006-mk-dist-freshness-guard/fix-design/fix-design.md:\n  Line 72: - Exact change: Add a case-insensitive mutating-tool classifier for write, edit, and apply_patch/apply-patch. In tool.execute.before, clear staleCache and staleCheckedAt for those tools before returning. Add tool.execute.after, supported by the SDK at .opencode/node_modules/@opencode-ai/plugin/dist/index.d.ts:249-258, and call refreshStale('source-mutation') after those tools. Refreshing all recognized file mutations is preferable to fragile patch-text parsing; the next system transform then uses the post-write result without waiting for the TTL.\n\n  Line 75: - Test: Extend mk-dist-freshness-guard.test.cjs with fresh-cache-then-edit, apply-patch, tool.execute.after, no-op mutation, and unrelated-tool cases; assert no console writes and no TTL delay.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/z_archive/047-agent-implement-code/research/stream-01-oh-my-opencode-slim/iterations/iteration-4.md:\n  Line 85: The returned plugin registers `agent`, `tool`, `mcp`, `config`, `event`, `tool.execute.before`, `command.execute.before`, `chat.headers`, `chat.message`, `experimental.chat.system.transform`, `experimental.chat.messages.transform`, and `tool.execute.after`. Evidence: `.opencode/specs/z_future/improved-agent-orchestration/external/oh-my-opencode-slim/src/index.ts:373`, `.opencode/specs/z_future/improved-agent-orchestration/external/oh-my-opencode-slim/src/index.ts:376`, `.opencode/specs/z_future/improved-agent-orchestration/external/oh-my-opencode-slim/src/index.ts:378`, `.opencode/specs/z_future/improved-agent-orchestration/external/oh-my-opencode-slim/src/index.ts:386`, `.opencode/specs/z_future/improved-agent-orchestration/external/oh-my-opencode-slim/src/index.ts:388`, `.opencode/specs/z_future/improved-agent-orchestration/external/oh-my-opencode-slim/src/index.ts:715`, `.opencode/specs/z_future/improved-agent-orchestration/external/oh-my-opencode-slim/src/index.ts:783`, `.opencode/specs/z_future/improved-agent-orchestration/external/oh-my-opencode-slim/src/index.ts:806`, `.opencode/specs/z_future/improved-agent-orchestration/external/oh-my-opencode-slim/src/index.ts:835`, `.opencode/specs/z_future/improved-agent-orchestration/external/oh-my-opencode-slim/src/index.ts:839`, `.opencode/specs/z_future/improved-agent-orchestration/external/oh-my-opencode-slim/src/index.ts:871`, `.opencode/specs/z_future/improved-agent-orchestration/external/oh-my-opencode-slim/src/index.ts:915`, `.opencode/specs/z_future/improved-agent-orchestration/external/oh-my-opencode-slim/src/index.ts:975`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/z_archive/047-agent-implement-code/research/stream-01-oh-my-opencode-slim/research.md:\n  Line 97: - **F-X-01.** Plugin startup composes enforcement through `src/index.ts`: registers `agent`, `tool`, `mcp`, `config`, `event`, `tool.execute.before`, `command.execute.before`, `chat.headers`, `chat.message`, `experimental.chat.system.transform`, `experimental.chat.messages.transform`, `tool.execute.after`. Hook ordering matters: message-transform first rewrites display-name mentions, then image attachments, todo continuation, task session reminders, phase reminders, available-skill filtering.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-speckit/z_archive/001-fix-command-dispatch/z_archive/077-speckit-upgrade-from-research/research/hooks-synthesis.md:\n  Line 101: | `tool.execute.after` hook     | Plugin API            | Cannot intercept tool results        |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/opencode-plugins-folder-purity.vitest.ts:\n  Line 25:   'tool.execute.after',\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-speckit/z_archive/020-mcp-working-memory-hybrid-rag/scratch/opencode-working-memory/AGENTS.md:\n  Line 240:     \"tool.execute.after\": async (ctx) => {\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-speckit/z_archive/020-mcp-working-memory-hybrid-rag/scratch/opencode-working-memory/index.ts:\n  Line 1632:     \"tool.execute.after\": async (hookInput, hookOutput) => {\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-speckit/z_archive/020-mcp-working-memory-hybrid-rag/scratch/opencode-working-memory/docs/architecture.md:\n  Line 111: Pruning happens in `tool.execute.after` hook before tool output enters conversation.\n\n  Line 317: 4. Update extraction heuristics in `tool.execute.after`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-speckit/z_archive/020-mcp-working-memory-hybrid-rag/research/136 - analysis-working-memory-hybrid-rag-systems.md:\n  Line 145: Tool execution → [Hook: tool.execute.after] → Pattern extraction \n\n  Line 218: 3. **Extraction hook** — Mirror `tool.execute.after` pattern to update working_memory table\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/031-deep-loop-gpt-reliability/001-research-and-diagnosis/001-gpt-behavioral-hardening-research/research/lineages/opus-critical/iterations/iteration-006.md:\n  Line 7: - `.opencode/node_modules/@opencode-ai/plugin/dist/index.d.ts:235-271` — `tool.execute.before`, `tool.execute.after`, `experimental.chat.*.transform` hook signatures\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/031-deep-loop-gpt-reliability/003-guard-and-enforcement/002-mk-deep-loop-guard-hardening/research/lineages/gpt-fast-high/deep-research-strategy.md:\n  Line 32: - A pure before-hook approach cannot reliably know whether a prior hand-off failed or timed out unless the plugin also records `tool.execute.after` data or the prompt carries an explicit retry token.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/031-deep-loop-gpt-reliability/003-guard-and-enforcement/002-mk-deep-loop-guard-hardening/research/lineages/gpt-fast-high/iterations/iteration-003.md:\n  Line 11: 3. A before-only counter can enforce exactly-one hand-off, but cannot know whether the first hand-off failed unless the plugin also records after-hook outcome. The SDK exposes `tool.execute.after` with `tool`, `sessionID`, `callID`, prior `args`, and output fields [SOURCE: .opencode/node_modules/@opencode-ai/plugin/dist/index.d.ts:249-258]. That is enough to attach outcomes to the before-hook ledger, even if the exact Task metadata shape needs implementation-time smoke testing.\n\n  Line 22: - Allow second hand-off only when the ledger marks the previous call as `error` or `timeout` from `tool.execute.after`, or when the prompt carries an explicit retry token such as `retry_of_callID=<prior-callID>`.\n\n  Line 40: - After-hook outcome attachment point from `tool.execute.after` [SOURCE: .opencode/node_modules/@opencode-ai/plugin/dist/index.d.ts:249-258].\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/031-deep-loop-gpt-reliability/003-guard-and-enforcement/002-mk-deep-loop-guard-hardening/research/lineages/gpt-fast-high/research.md:\n  Line 50: - Use `tool.execute.after` to update outcome for the same `callID`; the SDK exposes after-hook `sessionID`, `callID`, original `args`, `title`, `output`, and `metadata` [SOURCE: .opencode/node_modules/@opencode-ai/plugin/dist/index.d.ts:249-258].\n\n  Line 107: - Task `tool.execute.after` metadata should be smoke-tested to classify `ok|error|timeout` reliably.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-speckit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/004-shared-infrastructure/002-command-presentation-workflow-separation/006-presentation-adherence-research/research/iterations/iteration-011.md:\n  Line 3: **Verdict:** The true mechanical solution is not more prompt prose: render the `MEMORY:SEARCH` block in code from the normalized search envelope, then expose it as a last-mile tool output for the model to copy. Best path is JSON-safe renderer in memory_search plus OpenCode `tool.execute.after` pass-through/rewrite; final assistant post-processing is currently unproven and riskier.\n\n  Line 21: - Evidence: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/opencode-plugins-folder-purity.vitest.ts:25 'tool.execute.after',\n\n  Line 22: - Detail: The repo recognizes `tool.execute.after` as a valid OpenCode plugin hook, and archived plugin docs describe tool-output pruning before output enters conversation. That is the right mechanical place to replace a memory_search tool transcript with an exact `MEMORY:SEARCH` block without destabilizing MCP internals.\n\n  Line 23: - Recommendation: Prototype in `.opencode/plugins/mk-spec-memory.js`: on `tool.execute.after`, detect memory search/context tool names, parse output JSON, prefer `data.presentation.memorySearchText`, and set `hookOutput.output` to that exact text; fail open on parse errors.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-speckit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/006-operator-tooling/001-hook-parity/004-fix-opencode-plugin-loader-bridge/tasks.md:\n  Line 92: - [x] **T-30** Read `.opencode/node_modules/@opencode-ai/plugin/dist/index.d.ts` lines 142-260 (Hooks interface) and confirm hook-name mismatch. [EVIDENCE: OpenCode `Hooks` exposes `event`, `tool`, `chat.message`, `chat.params`, `chat.headers`, `permission.ask`, `command.execute.before`, `tool.execute.before`, `shell.env`, `tool.execute.after`, `experimental.chat.messages.transform`, `experimental.chat.system.transform`, `experimental.session.compacting`, and `experimental.text.complete`; it does not expose `onSessionStart`, `onUserPromptSubmitted`, or `onSessionEnd`.]\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-speckit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/006-operator-tooling/001-hook-parity/004-fix-opencode-plugin-loader-bridge/implementation-summary.md:\n  Line 84: Phase 4 read the installed OpenCode `Hooks` interface and confirmed the valid surfaces are `event`, `tool`, `chat.message`, `chat.params`, `chat.headers`, `permission.ask`, `command.execute.before`, `tool.execute.before`, `shell.env`, `tool.execute.after`, `experimental.chat.messages.transform`, `experimental.chat.system.transform`, `experimental.session.compacting`, and `experimental.text.complete`. The plugin was patched to mirror the compact plugin's event/system-transform pattern without modifying bridge/cache helpers.\n","metadata":{"matches":39,"truncated":false},"title":"tool\\.execute\\.after","time":{"start":1783744412469,"end":1783744412967}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0053605090bf5068016a51c79c61008191b112383a603b7437"}},"id":"prt_f4f73bb070019OmYlGhKBypaWh","sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","messageID":"msg_f4f737fd0001wRr7n18ON9wiv2"}}
