nal OpenCode plugins are justified, and which exact `tool.execute.before/after`, `session.*`, or `experimental.*` surfaces should host them?\n+- [x] Which additional OpenCode plugins are justified, and which exact `tool.execute.before/after`, `session.*`, or `experimental.*` surfaces should host them?\n - [ ] Which additional Claude hooks are justified, and which exact `PreToolUse`, `PostToolUse`, `SessionStart`, `UserPromptSubmit`, `Stop`, or `SessionEnd` surfaces should host them?\n - [ ] How should candidates be prioritized by value, feasibility, overlap, false-positive risk, and blast radius?\n - [ ] Which attractive ideas should be ruled out because the runtime surface is unsuitable or existing infrastructure already owns the behavior?\n <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n@@ -31,44 +31,51 @@\n <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n \n - Which skill contracts are plausible automation candidates? Candidate families are mutation intake (`system-spec-kit`), destructive command safety (`sk-git`), post-edit quality (`code-quality`), and route/lifecycle validation (`system-skill-advisor`, `system-deep-loop`).\n+- Which OpenCode plugins are justified? Six candidates now have exact surfaces: two pre-execution guards, one post-edit router, one MCP route guard, and two session-lifecycle sentinels.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n \n - Current plugin inventory plus source-skill contract reads efficiently separated gaps from already-shipped behavior. (iteration 1)\n+- Existing plugin implementations supplied reusable command extraction, fail-open behavior, cache, session cleanup, and context-injection patterns. (iteration 2)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n \n - The initial memory-context lookup timed out; repository evidence is the fallback.\n - Broad hook-term search was noisy because generated and archived artifacts dominated results. (iteration 1)\n+- Repository-wide `tool.execute.after` search included archived and sibling-lineage artifacts; current source and tests were required to resolve drift. (iteration 2)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n \n - Generic prompt-context plugin: overlaps advisor, memory, code-graph, and goal entrypoints. (iteration 1)\n - Hook-owned deep-loop convergence: violates mode-packet and runtime ownership. (iteration 1)\n+- Full quality suites after every mutation: too expensive for `tool.execute.after`. (iteration 2)\n+- Design-audit auto-scoring: lacks rendered and register evidence. (iteration 2)\n+- Blanket `mcp__*` blocking: breaks native MCP exemptions. (iteration 2)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n \n-None yet.\n+- Automatic full quality suites after every edit: path-specific lightweight checks are the viable form. (iteration 2)\n+- Automatic design-audit scores from file edits: a write hook cannot establish visual evidence. (iteration 2)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n ## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n \n - Completed pivots: 0\n - Failed pivots: 0\n - Saturated: none yet\n-- Remaining frontier: exact OpenCode mapping, Claude mapping, prioritization, and risk controls\n+- Remaining frontier: Claude mapping, prioritization, and cross-runtime risk controls\n <!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n ## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n@@ -79,9 +86,9 @@\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n \n-Map concrete OpenCode plugin candidates to `tool.execute.before/after`, `session.*`, or `experimental.*`, validating feasibility and overlap against current entrypoints.\n+Map equivalent Claude hooks, distinguishing true timing parity from runtime-specific approximations, then rank the combined candidate set.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n","additions":11,"deletions":4},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-dashboard.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-dashboard.md","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-dashboard.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-dashboard.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@ -2,33 +2,37 @@\n \n ## Status\n \n - Session: `fanout-gptsol-1783743995827-g7k8yl`\n-- Iterations: 1 / 5\n-- Questions answered: 1 / 5\n+- Iterations: 2 / 5\n+- Questions answered: 2 / 5\n - Stop policy: convergence\n-- Minimum iteration floor: not reached (1 / 3)\n+- Minimum iteration floor: not reached (2 / 3)\n \n ## Iterations\n \n | Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n |---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n | 1 | Skill and runtime inventory | 1.00 | 7 | complete |\n+| 2 | OpenCode plugin candidate mapping | 0.86 | 6 | complete |\n \n ## Trend\n \n-- Ratios: `1.00`\n-- Direction: insufficient history\n+- Ratios: `1.00 -> 0.86`\n+- Direction: descending, still high novelty\n \n ## Dead Ends\n \n - Generic prompt-context plugin.\n - Hook-owned deep-loop convergence.\n - Broad unscoped hook-term search.\n+- Full quality suite after every mutation.\n+- Design-audit auto-scoring from file edits.\n+- Blanket `mcp__*` blocking.\n \n ## Next Focus\n \n-Map concrete OpenCode plugin candidates to exact supported surfaces and validate overlap against current entrypoints.\n+Map equivalent Claude hooks, distinguish true parity from approximations, and rank the combined candidate set.\n \n ## Active Risks\n \n - Memory context unavailable after timeout; direct repository evidence is being used.\n","additions":10,"deletions":6}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nM .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/findings-registry.json\nM .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-strategy.md\nM .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-dashboard.md","time":{"start":1783744546079,"end":1783744546084}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08422b0e8d010228016a51c802b0448191b34a1317ef518c47"}},"id":"prt_f4f754a85001JWAQ9AqE6JM1zb","sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","messageID":"msg_f4f75410b001A02aw3lt2qXVkI"}}
