{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783744560611,"sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_R8iwqq1736cXwqaXDhWrUoyh","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":170},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy: Plugin and Hook Opportunities\n2: \n3: ## 2. TOPIC\n4: \n5: Identify additional OpenCode plugins and Claude hooks grounded in existing `.opencode/skills/` contracts, and map every candidate to a concrete supported runtime hook surface.\n6: \n7: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n8: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n9: \n10: - [x] Which existing skills contain repeatable enforcement, routing, recovery, or quality logic that is currently manual or prompt-dependent?\n11: - [x] Which additional OpenCode plugins are justified, and which exact `tool.execute.before/after`, `session.*`, or `experimental.*` surfaces should host them?\n12: - [ ] Which additional Claude hooks are justified, and which exact `PreToolUse`, `PostToolUse`, `SessionStart`, `UserPromptSubmit`, `Stop`, or `SessionEnd` surfaces should host them?\n13: - [ ] How should candidates be prioritized by value, feasibility, overlap, false-positive risk, and blast radius?\n14: - [ ] Which attractive ideas should be ruled out because the runtime surface is unsuitable or existing infrastructure already owns the behavior?\n15: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n16: \n17: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n18: \n19: - Do not implement plugins or hooks.\n20: - Do not propose candidates without a real skill source and concrete runtime surface.\n21: - Do not treat undocumented runtime events as available.\n22: - Do not modify files outside this detached lineage directory.\n23: \n24: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n25: \n26: - At least three evidence iterations have completed.\n27: - Every candidate is grounded in a cited skill and mapped to an allowed runtime surface.\n28: - OpenCode and Claude opportunities, prioritization, and eliminated alternatives are covered.\n29: - Convergence is legal under the configured policy, or five iterations have completed.\n30: \n31: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n32: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n33: \n34: - Which skill contracts are plausible automation candidates? Candidate families are mutation intake (`system-spec-kit`), destructive command safety (`sk-git`), post-edit quality (`code-quality`), and route/lifecycle validation (`system-skill-advisor`, `system-deep-loop`).\n35: - Which OpenCode plugins are justified? Six candidates now have exact surfaces: two pre-execution guards, one post-edit router, one MCP route guard, and two session-lifecycle sentinels.\n36: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n37: \n38: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n39: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n40: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n41: \n42: - Current plugin inventory plus source-skill contract reads efficiently separated gaps from already-shipped behavior. (iteration 1)\n43: - Existing plugin implementations supplied reusable command extraction, fail-open behavior, cache, session cleanup, and context-injection patterns. (iteration 2)\n44: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n45: \n46: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n47: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n48: \n49: - The initial memory-context lookup timed out; repository evidence is the fallback.\n50: - Broad hook-term search was noisy because generated and archived artifacts dominated results. (iteration 1)\n51: - Repository-wide `tool.execute.after` search included archived and sibling-lineage artifacts; current source and tests were required to resolve drift. (iteration 2)\n52: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n53: \n54: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n55: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n56: \n57: - Generic prompt-context plugin: overlaps advisor, memory, code-graph, and goal entrypoints. (iteration 1)\n58: - Hook-owned deep-loop convergence: violates mode-packet and runtime ownership. (iteration 1)\n59: - Full quality suites after every mutation: too expensive for `tool.execute.after`. (iteration 2)\n60: - Design-audit auto-scoring: lacks rendered and register evidence. (iteration 2)\n61: - Blanket `mcp__*` blocking: breaks native MCP exemptions. (iteration 2)\n62: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n63: \n64: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n65: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n66: \n67: - Automatic full quality suites after every edit: path-specific lightweight checks are the viable form. (iteration 2)\n68: - Automatic design-audit scores from file edits: a write hook cannot establish visual evidence. (iteration 2)\n69: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n70: \n71: <!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n72: ## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n73: \n74: - Completed pivots: 0\n75: - Failed pivots: 0\n76: - Saturated: none yet\n77: - Remaining frontier: Claude mapping, prioritization, and cross-runtime risk controls\n78: <!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n79: \n80: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n81: ## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n82: \n83: - Which OpenCode surface best fits each candidate while preserving current plugin ownership?\n84: - Which Claude surface provides equivalent timing without pretending runtime parity?\n85: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n86: \n87: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n88: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n89: \n90: Map equivalent Claude hooks, distinguishing true timing parity from runtime-specific approximations, then rank the combined candidate set.\n91: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n92: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n93: \n94: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n95: \n96: - The requested runtime surface set is closed: OpenCode `tool.execute.before/after`, `session.*`, `experimental.*`; Claude `PreToolUse`, `PostToolUse`, `SessionStart`, `UserPromptSubmit`, `Stop`, `SessionEnd`.\n97: - Every candidate must cite a real skill under `.opencode/skills/`.\n98: - Memory context was unavailable after timeout; direct repository evidence is authoritative for this lineage.\n99: \n100: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n101: \n102: - Max iterations: 5\n103: - Minimum iterations: 3\n104: - Convergence threshold: 0.05\n105: - Stop policy: convergence\n106: - Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n107: - Allowed write root: `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol`\n108: - Executor: `cli-opencode`, model `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast`\n109: - Session: `fanout-gptsol-1783743995827-g7k8yl`\n\n(End of file - total 109 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy: Plugin and Hook Opportunities\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n\nIdentify additional OpenCode plugins and Claude hooks grounded in existing `.opencode/skills/` contracts, and map every candidate to a concrete supported runtime hook surface.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n\n- [x] Which existing skills contain repeatable enforcement, routing, recovery, or quality logic that is currently manual or prompt-dependent?\n- [x] Which additional OpenCode plugins are justified, and which exact `tool.execute.before/after`, `session.*`, or `experimental.*` surfaces should host them?\n- [ ] Which additional Claude hooks are justified, and which exact `PreToolUse`, `PostToolUse`, `SessionStart`, `UserPromptSubmit`, `Stop`, or `SessionEnd` surfaces should host them?\n- [ ] How should candidates be prioritized by value, feasibility, overlap, false-positive risk, and blast radius?\n- [ ] Which attractive ideas should be ruled out because the runtime surface is unsuitable or existing infrastructure already owns the behavior?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do not implement plugins or hooks.\n- Do not propose candidates without a real skill source and concrete runtime surface.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy: Plugin and Hook Opportunities\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n\nIdentify additional OpenCode plugins and Claude hooks grounded in existing `.opencode/skills/` contracts, and map every candidate to a concrete supported runtime hook surface.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n\n- [x] Which existing skills contain repeatable enforcement, routing, recovery, or quality logic that is currently manual or prompt-dependent?\n- [x] Which additional OpenCode plugins are justified, and which exact `tool.execute.before/after`, `session.*`, or `experimental.*` surfaces should host them?\n- [ ] Which additional Claude hooks are justified, and which exact `PreToolUse`, `PostToolUse`, `SessionStart`, `UserPromptSubmit`, `Stop`, or `SessionEnd` surfaces should host them?\n- [ ] How should candidates be prioritized by value, feasibility, overlap, false-positive risk, and blast radius?\n- [ ] Which attractive ideas should be ruled out because the runtime surface is unsuitable or existing infrastructure already owns the behavior?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do not implement plugins or hooks.\n- Do not propose candidates without a real skill source and concrete runtime surface.\n- Do not treat undocumented runtime events as available.\n- Do not modify files outside this detached lineage directory.\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n\n- At least three evidence iterations have completed.\n- Every candidate is grounded in a cited skill and mapped to an allowed runtime surface.\n- OpenCode and Claude opportunities, prioritization, and eliminated alternatives are covered.\n- Convergence is legal under the configured policy, or five iterations have completed.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n\n- Which skill contracts are plausible automation candidates? Candidate families are mutation intake (`system-spec-kit`), destructive command safety (`sk-git`), post-edit quality (`code-quality`), and route/lifecycle validation (`system-skill-advisor`, `system-deep-loop`).\n- Which OpenCode plugins are justified? Six candidates now have exact surfaces: two pre-execution guards, one post-edit router, one MCP route guard, and two session-lifecycle sentinels.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n\n- Current plugin inventory plus source-skill contract reads efficiently separated gaps from already-shipped behavior. (iteration 1)\n- Existing plugin implementations supplied reusable command extraction, fail-open behavior, cache, session cleanup, and context-injection patterns. (iteration 2)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n\n- The initial memory-context lookup timed out; repository evidence is the fallback.\n- Broad hook-term search was noisy because generated and archived artifacts dominated results. (iteration 1)\n- Repository-wide `tool.execute.after` search included archived and sibling-lineage artifacts; current source and tests were required to resolve drift. (iteration 2)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n\n- Generic prompt-context plugin: overlaps advisor, memory, code-graph, and goal entrypoints. (iteration 1)\n- Hook-owned deep-loop convergence: violates mode-packet and runtime ownership. (iteration 1)\n- Full quality suites after every mutation: too expensive for `tool.execute.after`. (iteration 2)\n- Design-audit auto-scoring: lacks rendered and register evidence. (iteration 2)\n- Blanket `mcp__*` blocking: breaks native MCP exemptions. (iteration 2)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n\n- Automatic full quality suites after every edit: path-specific lightweight checks are the viable form. (iteration 2)\n- Automatic design-audit scores from file edits: a write hook cannot establish visual evidence. (iteration 2)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Saturated: none yet\n- Remaining frontier: Claude mapping, prioritization, and cross-runtime risk controls\n<!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n\n- Which OpenCode surface best fits each candidate while preserving current plugin ownership?\n- Which Claude surface provides equivalent timing without pretending runtime parity?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n\nMap equivalent Claude hooks, distinguishing true timing parity from runtime-specific approximations, then rank the combined candidate set.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n\n- The requested runtime surface set is closed: OpenCode `tool.execute.before/after`, `session.*`, `experimental.*`; Claude `PreToolUse`, `PostToolUse`, `SessionStart`, `UserPromptSubmit`, `Stop`, `SessionEnd`.\n- Every candidate must cite a real skill under `.opencode/skills/`.\n- Memory context was unavailable after timeout; direct repository evidence is authoritative for this lineage.\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n\n- Max iterations: 5\n- Minimum iterations: 3\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05\n- Stop policy: convergence\n- Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n- Allowed write root: `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol`\n- Executor: `cli-opencode`, model `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast`\n- Session: `fanout-gptsol-1783743995827-g7k8yl`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":109,"totalLines":109,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1783744560604,"end":1783744560608}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d39ffbb429655bb016a51c83080b881918e29569dc9c34939"}},"id":"prt_f4f75fddb0011WvNwe3vX1dg5K","sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","messageID":"msg_f4f75c97b001GFqQeJNbRrrbHd"}}
