ty hook rather than adding another entry.\",\n+      \"surface\": \"PostToolUse/Write|Edit\",\n+      \"skill\": \"sk-code/code-quality\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"f-iter003-cl4\",\n+      \"iteration\": 3,\n+      \"summary\": \"Claude External MCP Route Guard requires generated external-family matchers.\",\n+      \"surface\": \"PreToolUse/external MCP matchers\",\n+      \"skill\": \"mcp-code-mode\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"f-iter003-cl5\",\n+      \"iteration\": 3,\n+      \"summary\": \"Claude Completion Evidence Sentinel extends the existing Stop owner.\",\n+      \"surface\": \"Stop\",\n+      \"skill\": \"system-spec-kit + sk-code/code-quality\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"f-iter003-cl6\",\n+      \"iteration\": 3,\n+      \"summary\": \"Incremental code-graph freshness maps to PostToolUse and tool.execute.after.\",\n+      \"surface\": \"PostToolUse/Write|Edit + tool.execute.after\",\n+      \"skill\": \"system-code-graph\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"f-iter003-priority\",\n+      \"iteration\": 3,\n+      \"summary\": \"Priority order is git safety, spec mutation, post-edit quality, graph freshness, completion evidence, MCP routing, then readiness priming.\"\n     }\n   ],\n   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n     \"generic prompt-context plugin\",\n     \"hook-owned deep-loop convergence\",\n     \"full quality suite after every tool\",\n     \"design-audit auto-scoring after edits\",\n-    \"blocking all mcp__ calls\"\n+    \"blocking all mcp__ calls\",\n+    \"second quality PostToolUse entry\",\n+    \"second UserPromptSubmit advisor\",\n+    \"SessionEnd completion verification\",\n+    \"Stop-time test execution\",\n+    \"shared cross-runtime transport implementation\"\n   ],\n   \"metrics\": {\n-    \"iterationsCompleted\": 2,\n-    \"openQuestions\": 3,\n-    \"resolvedQuestions\": 2,\n-    \"keyFindings\": 8,\n-    \"convergenceScore\": 0.4,\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 3,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 0,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 5,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 15,\n+    \"convergenceScore\": 1,\n     \"coverageBySources\": {\n       \"plugin-docs\": 1,\n       \"skill-contracts\": 9,\n-      \"plugin-implementations\": 3\n+      \"plugin-implementations\": 3,\n+      \"claude-wiring\": 5,\n+      \"runtime-hook-contracts\": 2\n     }\n   },\n   \"rejectedPatterns\": [],\n   \"suppressedCandidates\": [],\n@@ -92,6 +146,14 @@\n     \"completed\": [],\n     \"failures\": [],\n     \"overrides\": [],\n     \"saturatedDirections\": []\n+  },\n+  \"status\": \"converged\",\n+  \"stopReason\": \"converged\",\n+  \"qualityGuards\": {\n+    \"sourceDiversity\": true,\n+    \"focusAlignment\": true,\n+    \"noSingleWeakSource\": true,\n+    \"questionCoverage\": true\n   }\n }\n","additions":73,"deletions":11},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-strategy.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-strategy.md","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -8,11 +8,11 @@\n ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n \n - [x] Which existing skills contain repeatable enforcement, routing, recovery, or quality logic that is currently manual or prompt-dependent?\n - [x] Which additional OpenCode plugins are justified, and which exact `tool.execute.before/after`, `session.*`, or `experimental.*` surfaces should host them?\n-- [ ] Which additional Claude hooks are justified, and which exact `PreToolUse`, `PostToolUse`, `SessionStart`, `UserPromptSubmit`, `Stop`, or `SessionEnd` surfaces should host them?\n-- [ ] How should candidates be prioritized by value, feasibility, overlap, false-positive risk, and blast radius?\n-- [ ] Which attractive ideas should be ruled out because the runtime surface is unsuitable or existing infrastructure already owns the behavior?\n+- [x] Which additional Claude hooks are justified, and which exact `PreToolUse`, `PostToolUse`, `SessionStart`, `UserPromptSubmit`, `Stop`, or `SessionEnd` surfaces should host them?\n+- [x] How should candidates be prioritized by value, feasibility, overlap, false-positive risk, and blast radius?\n+- [x] Which attractive ideas should be ruled out because the runtime surface is unsuitable or existing infrastructure already owns the behavior?\n <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n \n ## 4. NON-GOALS\n \n@@ -32,24 +32,29 @@\n ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n \n - Which skill contracts are plausible automation candidates? Candidate families are mutation intake (`system-spec-kit`), destructive command safety (`sk-git`), post-edit quality (`code-quality`), and route/lifecycle validation (`system-skill-advisor`, `system-deep-loop`).\n - Which OpenCode plugins are justified? Six candidates now have exact surfaces: two pre-execution guards, one post-edit router, one MCP route guard, and two session-lifecycle sentinels.\n+- Which Claude hooks are justified? Six mappings use `UserPromptSubmit`, `PreToolUse`, `PostToolUse`, and `Stop`; duplicate `SessionStart`/`SessionEnd` work is deliberately avoided.\n+- How should candidates be prioritized? Git safety and spec mutation lead, followed by post-edit quality and graph freshness; semantic sentinels remain advisory-first.\n+- Which ideas should be eliminated? Duplicate hook registrations, broad per-edit suites, evidence-free design scoring, blanket MCP blocking, Stop-time tests, and shared transport adapters are unsuitable.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n \n - Current plugin inventory plus source-skill contract reads efficiently separated gaps from already-shipped behavior. (iteration 1)\n - Existing plugin implementations supplied reusable command extraction, fail-open behavior, cache, session cleanup, and context-injection patterns. (iteration 2)\n+- Live Claude settings and source hooks exposed actual matcher, timeout, ownership, and deny/advisory contracts. (iteration 3)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n \n - The initial memory-context lookup timed out; repository evidence is the fallback.\n - Broad hook-term search was noisy because generated and archived artifacts dominated results. (iteration 1)\n - Repository-wide `tool.execute.after` search included archived and sibling-lineage artifacts; current source and tests were required to resolve drift. (iteration 2)\n+- A settings glob missed `.claude/settings.json`; exact search and read recovered the live wiring. (iteration 3)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n@@ -58,37 +63,41 @@\n - Hook-owned deep-loop convergence: violates mode-packet and runtime ownership. (iteration 1)\n - Full quality suites after every mutation: too expensive for `tool.execute.after`. (iteration 2)\n - Design-audit auto-scoring: lacks rendered and register evidence. (iteration 2)\n - Blanket `mcp__*` blocking: breaks native MCP exemptions. (iteration 2)\n+- Duplicate Claude hook entries: extend existing owners to avoid duplicate execution and ordering ambiguity. (iteration 3)\n+- SessionEnd completion verification and Stop-time tests: wrong lifecycle timing or unbounded cost. (iteration 3)\n+- Shared transport adapter across runtimes: parity belongs in shared policy cores, not event adapters. (iteration 3)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n \n - Automatic full quality suites after every edit: path-specific lightweight checks are the viable form. (iteration 2)\n - Automatic design-audit scores from file edits: a write hook cannot establish visual evidence. (iteration 2)\n+- Duplicate PostToolUse/UserPromptSubmit registrations: extend the existing source-skill owner. (iteration 3)\n+- SessionEnd completion checks and Stop-time test execution: too late or too expensive. (iteration 3)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n ## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n \n - Completed pivots: 0\n - Failed pivots: 0\n - Saturated: none yet\n-- Remaining frontier: Claude mapping, prioritization, and cross-runtime risk controls\n+- Remaining frontier: implementation smoke tests only; research questions are saturated\n <!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n ## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n \n-- Which OpenCode surface best fits each candidate while preserving current plugin ownership?\n-- Which Claude surface provides equivalent timing without pretending runtime parity?\n+None. Implementation validation gaps are retained in the synthesis.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n \n-Map equivalent Claude hooks, distinguishing true timing parity from runtime-specific approximations, then rank the combined candidate set.\n+Converged after iteration 3: synthesize the ranked cross-runtime roadmap and implementation validation gaps.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n","additions":16,"deletions":7},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-dashboard.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-dashboard.md","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-dashboard.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-dashboard.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@ -2,24 +2,26 @@\n \n ## Status\n \n - Session: `fanout-gptsol-1783743995827-g7k8yl`\n-- Iterations: 2 / 5\n-- Questions answered: 2 / 5\n+- Iterations: 3 / 5\n+- Questions answered: 5 / 5\n - Stop policy: convergence\n-- Minimum iteration floor: not reached (2 / 3)\n+- Minimum iteration floor: passed (3 / 3)\n+- Stop reason: converged (`all_questions_answered`)\n \n ## Iterations\n \n | Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n |---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n | 1 | Skill and runtime inventory | 1.00 | 7 | complete |\n | 2 | OpenCode plugin candidate mapping | 0.86 | 6 | complete |\n+| 3 | Claude mapping and prioritization | 0.72 | 7 | complete |\n \n ## Trend\n \n-- Ratios: `1.00 -> 0.86`\n-- Direction: descending, still high novelty\n+- Ratios: `1.00 -> 0.86 -> 0.72`\n+- Direction: descending; legal stop came from complete question coverage, not low novelty\n \n ## Dead Ends\n \n - Generic prompt-context plugin.\n@@ -27,13 +29,17 @@\n - Broad unscoped hook-term search.\n - Full quality suite after every mutation.\n - Design-audit auto-scoring from file edits.\n - Blanket `mcp__*` blocking.\n+- Duplicate Claude hook registrations.\n+- SessionEnd completion verification and Stop-time tests.\n+- Shared cross-runtime transport adapters.\n \n ## Next Focus\n \n-Map equivalent Claude hooks, distinguish true parity from approximations, and rank the combined candidate set.\n+Synthesis complete; implementation planning should start with shared policy cores and runtime-specific adapters.\n \n ## Active Risks\n \n - Memory context unavailable after timeout; direct repository evidence is being used.\n - Fan-out override is not accepted by the stock reducer CLI, so workflow-owned reducer projections are refreshed directly inside this isolated lineage.\n+- Implementation-time smoke tests remain for matcher composition, Stop semantics, after-hook output, and graph debounce behavior.\n","additions":12,"deletions":6},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-state.jsonl","relativePath":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-state.jsonl","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-state.jsonl\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-state.jsonl\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/deep-research-state.jsonl\n@@ -1,4 +1,6 @@\n {\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"What additional OpenCode plugins and Claude hooks could we build based on existing repo skills? Ground every candidate in a real skill under .opencode/skills/ and name its concrete runtime surface (OpenCode plugin hook: tool.execute.before/after, session.*, experimental.*; or Claude hook: PreToolUse/PostToolUse/SessionStart/UserPromptSubmit/Stop/SessionEnd).\",\"maxIterations\":5,\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"antiConvergence\":{\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"stopPolicy\":\"convergence\"},\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-07-11T04:29:38Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities\",\"artifactDir\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gptsol-1783743995827-g7k8yl\",\"generation\":1,\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}\n {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":1,\"run\":1,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"newInfoRatio\":1.0,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Skill and runtime inventory\",\"findingsCount\":7,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Seven distinct current-state findings established the baseline inventory, ownership boundaries, and four high-value automation families with no prior iteration evidence.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Which skill contracts are plausible automation candidates?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Which skill contracts are plausible automation candidates?\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"generic prompt-context plugin\",\"hook-owned deep-loop convergence\"],\"toolsUsed\":[\"Glob\",\"Grep\",\"Read\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\".opencode/plugins/README.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/SKI