{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783744767101,"sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_u8TEB1r4lMuf5zCyG7Mqy8vV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/research.md","offset":1,"limit":300},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/research.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Research: Additional OpenCode Plugins and Claude Hooks\n2: \n3: ## Executive Summary\n4: \n5: Research is in progress. The first iteration established that the strongest uncovered automation boundaries are mutation intake, destructive shell/git commands, post-edit quality checks, and stop-time completion evidence. Existing prompt-context and deep-loop lifecycle behavior should be extended through their owning skills rather than duplicated.\n6: \n7: ## Current Evidence\n8: \n9: - OpenCode plugin entrypoints are intentionally minimal and delegate bridge logic to owning skills. [SOURCE: .opencode/plugins/README.md:24-38]\n10: - Current plugins already cover advisor, code graph, memory, goals, deep-loop dispatch, dist freshness, and cleanup. [SOURCE: .opencode/plugins/README.md:42-52]\n11: - Candidate source skills: `system-spec-kit`, `code-quality`, `sk-git`, `system-skill-advisor`, and `system-deep-loop`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md:28-61] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/SKILL.md:54-136] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-git/SKILL.md:291-317]\n12: \n13: ## OpenCode Candidate Set\n14: \n15: | Candidate | Skill grounding | Exact surface | Initial posture |\n16: |---|---|---|---|\n17: | Spec Mutation Gate | `system-spec-kit` | `tool.execute.before` | block missing Gate 3 only |\n18: | Git Safety Guard | `sk-git` | `tool.execute.before` | block unambiguous destructive forms; warn otherwise |\n19: | Post-Edit Quality Router | `sk-code/code-quality` | `tool.execute.after` + `experimental.chat.system.transform` | advisory, cheap checks |\n20: | External MCP Route Guard | `mcp-code-mode` | `tool.execute.before` | warn-first with native allowlist |\n21: | Completion Evidence Sentinel | `system-spec-kit`, `code-quality` | `session.idle` + `experimental.chat.system.transform` | advisory |\n22: | Session Readiness Primer | `system-spec-kit`, `system-skill-advisor` | `session.created` + `experimental.chat.system.transform` | advisory, one-shot |\n23: | Incremental Code-Graph Freshness | `system-code-graph` | `tool.execute.after` | warm-only, debounced |\n24: \n25: ## Claude Candidate Set\n26: \n27: | Candidate | Skill grounding | Exact surface | Initial posture |\n28: |---|---|---|---|\n29: | Spec Mutation Gate | `system-spec-kit` | `UserPromptSubmit` + `PreToolUse/Write|Edit|Bash` | classify then enforce |\n30: | Git Safety Guard | `sk-git` | `PreToolUse/Bash` | block exact destructive forms |\n31: | Expanded Post-Edit Quality Router | `sk-code/code-quality` | `PostToolUse/Write|Edit` | extend existing warn-only hook |\n32: | External MCP Route Guard | `mcp-code-mode` | `PreToolUse` external MCP matchers | manifest allowlist, warn-first |\n33: | Completion Evidence Sentinel | `system-spec-kit`, `code-quality` | `Stop` | verify recorded evidence only |\n34: | Incremental Code-Graph Freshness | `system-code-graph` | `PostToolUse/Write|Edit` | warm-only, debounced |\n35: \n36: ## Priority Roadmap\n37: \n38: 1. Git Safety Guard.\n39: 2. Spec Mutation Gate.\n40: 3. Expanded Post-Edit Quality Router.\n41: 4. Incremental Code-Graph Freshness.\n42: 5. Completion Evidence Sentinel.\n43: 6. External MCP Route Guard.\n44: 7. Session Readiness Primer.\n45: \n46: ## Eliminated Alternatives\n47: \n48: - Another generic prompt-context injector.\n49: - Hook-owned deep-loop convergence or synthesis.\n50: - Full quality suites after every tool execution.\n51: - Design-audit auto-scoring without rendered evidence.\n52: - A blanket block on all `mcp__*` tools.\n53: - Duplicate Claude PostToolUse or UserPromptSubmit registrations where an existing owner can be extended.\n54: - SessionEnd completion verification and Stop-time test execution.\n55: - Shared transport code across Claude and OpenCode; share policy cores only.\n56: \n57: ## Open Questions\n58: \n59: - Exact OpenCode and Claude hook mappings.\n60: - Candidate ranking and false-positive controls.\n61: - Additional eliminated alternatives.\n\n(End of file - total 61 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Research: Additional OpenCode Plugins and Claude Hooks\n\n## Executive Summary\n\nResearch is in progress. The first iteration established that the strongest uncovered automation boundaries are mutation intake, destructive shell/git commands, post-edit quality checks, and stop-time completion evidence. Existing prompt-context and deep-loop lifecycle behavior should be extended through their owning skills rather than duplicated.\n\n## Current Evidence\n\n- OpenCode plugin entrypoints are intentionally minimal and delegate bridge logic to owning skills. [SOURCE: .opencode/plugins/README.md:24-38]\n- Current plugins already cover advisor, code graph, memory, goals, deep-loop dispatch, dist freshness, and cleanup. [SOURCE: .opencode/plugins/README.md:42-52]\n- Candidate source skills: `system-spec-kit`, `code-quality`, `sk-git`, `system-skill-advisor`, and `system-deep-loop`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md:28-61] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/SKILL.md:54-136] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-git/SKILL.md:291-317]\n\n## OpenCode Candidate Set\n\n| Candidate | Skill grounding | Exact surface | Initial posture |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Spec Mutation Gate | `system-spec-kit` | `tool.execute.before` | block missing Gate 3 only |\n| Git Safety Guard | `sk-git` | `tool.execute.before` | block unambiguous destructive forms; warn otherwise |\n| Post-Edit Quality Router | `sk-code/code-quality` | `tool.execute.after` + `experimental.chat.system.transform` | advisory, cheap checks |\n| External MCP Route Guard | `mcp-code-mode` | `tool.execute.before` | warn-first with native allowlist |","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/research.md","text":"# Research: Additional OpenCode Plugins and Claude Hooks\n\n## Executive Summary\n\nResearch is in progress. The first iteration established that the strongest uncovered automation boundaries are mutation intake, destructive shell/git commands, post-edit quality checks, and stop-time completion evidence. Existing prompt-context and deep-loop lifecycle behavior should be extended through their owning skills rather than duplicated.\n\n## Current Evidence\n\n- OpenCode plugin entrypoints are intentionally minimal and delegate bridge logic to owning skills. [SOURCE: .opencode/plugins/README.md:24-38]\n- Current plugins already cover advisor, code graph, memory, goals, deep-loop dispatch, dist freshness, and cleanup. [SOURCE: .opencode/plugins/README.md:42-52]\n- Candidate source skills: `system-spec-kit`, `code-quality`, `sk-git`, `system-skill-advisor`, and `system-deep-loop`. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md:28-61] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/SKILL.md:54-136] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-git/SKILL.md:291-317]\n\n## OpenCode Candidate Set\n\n| Candidate | Skill grounding | Exact surface | Initial posture |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Spec Mutation Gate | `system-spec-kit` | `tool.execute.before` | block missing Gate 3 only |\n| Git Safety Guard | `sk-git` | `tool.execute.before` | block unambiguous destructive forms; warn otherwise |\n| Post-Edit Quality Router | `sk-code/code-quality` | `tool.execute.after` + `experimental.chat.system.transform` | advisory, cheap checks |\n| External MCP Route Guard | `mcp-code-mode` | `tool.execute.before` | warn-first with native allowlist |\n| Completion Evidence Sentinel | `system-spec-kit`, `code-quality` | `session.idle` + `experimental.chat.system.transform` | advisory |\n| Session Readiness Primer | `system-spec-kit`, `system-skill-advisor` | `session.created` + `experimental.chat.system.transform` | advisory, one-shot |\n| Incremental Code-Graph Freshness | `system-code-graph` | `tool.execute.after` | warm-only, debounced |\n\n## Claude Candidate Set\n\n| Candidate | Skill grounding | Exact surface | Initial posture |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Spec Mutation Gate | `system-spec-kit` | `UserPromptSubmit` + `PreToolUse/Write|Edit|Bash` | classify then enforce |\n| Git Safety Guard | `sk-git` | `PreToolUse/Bash` | block exact destructive forms |\n| Expanded Post-Edit Quality Router | `sk-code/code-quality` | `PostToolUse/Write|Edit` | extend existing warn-only hook |\n| External MCP Route Guard | `mcp-code-mode` | `PreToolUse` external MCP matchers | manifest allowlist, warn-first |\n| Completion Evidence Sentinel | `system-spec-kit`, `code-quality` | `Stop` | verify recorded evidence only |\n| Incremental Code-Graph Freshness | `system-code-graph` | `PostToolUse/Write|Edit` | warm-only, debounced |\n\n## Priority Roadmap\n\n1. Git Safety Guard.\n2. Spec Mutation Gate.\n3. Expanded Post-Edit Quality Router.\n4. Incremental Code-Graph Freshness.\n5. Completion Evidence Sentinel.\n6. External MCP Route Guard.\n7. Session Readiness Primer.\n\n## Eliminated Alternatives\n\n- Another generic prompt-context injector.\n- Hook-owned deep-loop convergence or synthesis.\n- Full quality suites after every tool execution.\n- Design-audit auto-scoring without rendered evidence.\n- A blanket block on all `mcp__*` tools.\n- Duplicate Claude PostToolUse or UserPromptSubmit registrations where an existing owner can be extended.\n- SessionEnd completion verification and Stop-time test execution.\n- Shared transport code across Claude and OpenCode; share policy cores only.\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- Exact OpenCode and Claude hook mappings.\n- Candidate ranking and false-positive controls.\n- Additional eliminated alternatives.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":61,"totalLines":61,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/133-plugin-hook-opportunities/research/lineages/gptsol/research.md","time":{"start":1783744767096,"end":1783744767100}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b46974603520bf2016a51c8fe32148191a9d623890d7e848e"}},"id":"prt_f4f7920fd0010YKzdVwdXjySPh","sessionID":"ses_0b0929e3affe1FHkKX9E1sdw9Y","messageID":"msg_f4f790304001ZrmGugBvnkVoN8"}}
